34/// Return the best known alignment for an unknown pointer to a
35/// particular class.
36CharUnits CodeGenModule::getClassPointerAlignment(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
37 if (!RD->isCompleteDefinition())
38 return CharUnits::One(); // Hopefully won't be used anywhere.
39
40 auto &layout = getContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
41
42 // If the class is final, then we know that the pointer points to an
43 // object of that type and can use the full alignment.
44 if (RD->hasAttr<FinalAttr>()) {
45 return layout.getAlignment();
46
47 // Otherwise, we have to assume it could be a subclass.
48 } else {
49 return layout.getNonVirtualAlignment();
50 }
51}
52
53/// Return the best known alignment for a pointer to a virtual base,
54/// given the alignment of a pointer to the derived class.
55CharUnits CodeGenModule::getVBaseAlignment(CharUnits actualDerivedAlign,
56 const CXXRecordDecl *derivedClass,
57 const CXXRecordDecl *vbaseClass) {
58 // The basic idea here is that an underaligned derived pointer might
59 // indicate an underaligned base pointer.
60
61 assert(vbaseClass->isCompleteDefinition());
62 auto &baseLayout = getContext().getASTRecordLayout(vbaseClass);
63 CharUnits expectedVBaseAlign = baseLayout.getNonVirtualAlignment();
64
65 return getDynamicOffsetAlignment(actualDerivedAlign, derivedClass,
66 expectedVBaseAlign);
67}
68
69CharUnits
70CodeGenModule::getDynamicOffsetAlignment(CharUnits actualBaseAlign,
71 const CXXRecordDecl *baseDecl,
72 CharUnits expectedTargetAlign) {
73 // If the base is an incomplete type (which is, alas, possible with
74 // member pointers), be pessimistic.
75 if (!baseDecl->isCompleteDefinition())
76 return std::min(actualBaseAlign, expectedTargetAlign);
77
78 auto &baseLayout = getContext().getASTRecordLayout(baseDecl);
79 CharUnits expectedBaseAlign = baseLayout.getNonVirtualAlignment();
80
81 // If the class is properly aligned, assume the target offset is, too.
82 //
83 // This actually isn't necessarily the right thing to do --- if the
84 // class is a complete object, but it's only properly aligned for a
85 // base subobject, then the alignments of things relative to it are
86 // probably off as well. (Note that this requires the alignment of
87 // the target to be greater than the NV alignment of the derived
88 // class.)
89 //
90 // However, our approach to this kind of under-alignment can only
91 // ever be best effort; after all, we're never going to propagate
92 // alignments through variables or parameters. Note, in particular,
93 // that constructing a polymorphic type in an address that's less
94 // than pointer-aligned will generally trap in the constructor,
95 // unless we someday add some sort of attribute to change the
96 // assumed alignment of 'this'. So our goal here is pretty much
97 // just to allow the user to explicitly say that a pointer is
98 // under-aligned and then safely access its fields and vtables.
99 if (actualBaseAlign >= expectedBaseAlign) {
100 return expectedTargetAlign;
101 }
102
103 // Otherwise, we might be offset by an arbitrary multiple of the
104 // actual alignment. The correct adjustment is to take the min of
105 // the two alignments.
106 return std::min(actualBaseAlign, expectedTargetAlign);
107}
108
109Address CodeGenFunction::LoadCXXThisAddress() {
110 assert(CurFuncDecl && "loading 'this' without a func declaration?");
111 assert(isa<CXXMethodDecl>(CurFuncDecl));
112
113 // Lazily compute CXXThisAlignment.
114 if (CXXThisAlignment.isZero()) {
115 // Just use the best known alignment for the parent.
116 // TODO: if we're currently emitting a complete-object ctor/dtor,
117 // we can always use the complete-object alignment.
118 auto RD = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(CurFuncDecl)->getParent();
119 CXXThisAlignment = CGM.getClassPointerAlignment(RD);
120 }
121
122 return Address(LoadCXXThis(), CXXThisAlignment);
123}

125/// Emit the address of a field using a member data pointer.
126///
127/// \param E Only used for emergency diagnostics
128Address
129CodeGenFunction::EmitCXXMemberDataPointerAddress(const Expr *E, Address base,
130 llvm::Value *memberPtr,
131 const MemberPointerType *memberPtrType,
132 LValueBaseInfo *BaseInfo,
133 TBAAAccessInfo *TBAAInfo) {
134 // Ask the ABI to compute the actual address.
135 llvm::Value *ptr =
136 CGM.getCXXABI().EmitMemberDataPointerAddress(*this, E, base,
137 memberPtr, memberPtrType);
138
139 QualType memberType = memberPtrType->getPointeeType();
140 CharUnits memberAlign = getNaturalTypeAlignment(memberType, BaseInfo,
141 TBAAInfo);
142 memberAlign =
143 CGM.getDynamicOffsetAlignment(base.getAlignment(),
144 memberPtrType->getClass()->getAsCXXRecordDecl(),
145 memberAlign);
146 return Address(ptr, memberAlign);
147}
148
149CharUnits CodeGenModule::computeNonVirtualBaseClassOffset(
150 const CXXRecordDecl *DerivedClass, CastExpr::path_const_iterator Start,
151 CastExpr::path_const_iterator End) {
152 CharUnits Offset = CharUnits::Zero();
153
154 const ASTContext &Context = getContext();
155 const CXXRecordDecl *RD = DerivedClass;
156
157 for (CastExpr::path_const_iterator I = Start; I != End; ++I) {
158 const CXXBaseSpecifier *Base = *I;
159 assert(!Base->isVirtual() && "Should not see virtual bases here!");
160
161 // Get the layout.
162 const ASTRecordLayout &Layout = Context.getASTRecordLayout(RD);
163
164 const CXXRecordDecl *BaseDecl =
165 cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Base->getType()->getAs<RecordType>()->getDecl());
166
167 // Add the offset.
168 Offset += Layout.getBaseClassOffset(BaseDecl);
169
170 RD = BaseDecl;
171 }
172
173 return Offset;
174}
175
176llvm::Constant *
177CodeGenModule::GetNonVirtualBaseClassOffset(const CXXRecordDecl *ClassDecl,
178 CastExpr::path_const_iterator PathBegin,
179 CastExpr::path_const_iterator PathEnd) {
180 assert(PathBegin != PathEnd && "Base path should not be empty!");
181
182 CharUnits Offset =
183 computeNonVirtualBaseClassOffset(ClassDecl, PathBegin, PathEnd);
184 if (Offset.isZero())
185 return nullptr;
186
187 llvm::Type *PtrDiffTy =
188 Types.ConvertType(getContext().getPointerDiffType());
189
190 return llvm::ConstantInt::get(PtrDiffTy, Offset.getQuantity());
191}

193/// Gets the address of a direct base class within a complete object.
194/// This should only be used for (1) non-virtual bases or (2) virtual bases
195/// when the type is known to be complete (e.g. in complete destructors).
196///
197/// The object pointed to by 'This' is assumed to be non-null.
198Address
199CodeGenFunction::GetAddressOfDirectBaseInCompleteClass(Address This,
200 const CXXRecordDecl *Derived,
201 const CXXRecordDecl *Base,
202 bool BaseIsVirtual) {
203 // 'this' must be a pointer (in some address space) to Derived.
204 assert(This.getElementType() == ConvertType(Derived));
205
206 // Compute the offset of the virtual base.
207 CharUnits Offset;
208 const ASTRecordLayout &Layout = getContext().getASTRecordLayout(Derived);
209 if (BaseIsVirtual)
210 Offset = Layout.getVBaseClassOffset(Base);
211 else
212 Offset = Layout.getBaseClassOffset(Base);
213
214 // Shift and cast down to the base type.
215 // TODO: for complete types, this should be possible with a GEP.
216 Address V = This;
217 if (!Offset.isZero()) {
218 V = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(V, Int8Ty);
219 V = Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(V, Offset);
220 }
221 V = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(V, ConvertType(Base));
222
223 return V;
224}
225
226static Address
227ApplyNonVirtualAndVirtualOffset(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address addr,
228 CharUnits nonVirtualOffset,
229 llvm::Value *virtualOffset,
230 const CXXRecordDecl *derivedClass,
231 const CXXRecordDecl *nearestVBase) {
232 // Assert that we have something to do.
233 assert(!nonVirtualOffset.isZero() || virtualOffset != nullptr);
234
235 // Compute the offset from the static and dynamic components.
236 llvm::Value *baseOffset;
237 if (!nonVirtualOffset.isZero()) {
238 baseOffset = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.PtrDiffTy,
239 nonVirtualOffset.getQuantity());
240 if (virtualOffset) {
241 baseOffset = CGF.Builder.CreateAdd(virtualOffset, baseOffset);
242 }
243 } else {
244 baseOffset = virtualOffset;
245 }
246
247 // Apply the base offset.
248 llvm::Value *ptr = addr.getPointer();
249 ptr = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(ptr, CGF.Int8PtrTy);
250 ptr = CGF.Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(ptr, baseOffset, "add.ptr");
251
252 // If we have a virtual component, the alignment of the result will
253 // be relative only to the known alignment of that vbase.
254 CharUnits alignment;
255 if (virtualOffset) {
256 assert(nearestVBase && "virtual offset without vbase?");
257 alignment = CGF.CGM.getVBaseAlignment(addr.getAlignment(),
258 derivedClass, nearestVBase);
259 } else {
260 alignment = addr.getAlignment();
261 }
262 alignment = alignment.alignmentAtOffset(nonVirtualOffset);
263
264 return Address(ptr, alignment);
265}
266
267Address CodeGenFunction::GetAddressOfBaseClass(
268 Address Value, const CXXRecordDecl *Derived,
269 CastExpr::path_const_iterator PathBegin,
270 CastExpr::path_const_iterator PathEnd, bool NullCheckValue,
271 SourceLocation Loc) {
272 assert(PathBegin != PathEnd && "Base path should not be empty!");
273
274 CastExpr::path_const_iterator Start = PathBegin;
275 const CXXRecordDecl *VBase = nullptr;
276
277 // Sema has done some convenient canonicalization here: if the
278 // access path involved any virtual steps, the conversion path will
279 // *start* with a step down to the correct virtual base subobject,
280 // and hence will not require any further steps.
281 if ((*Start)->isVirtual()) {
282 VBase =
283 cast<CXXRecordDecl>((*Start)->getType()->getAs<RecordType>()->getDecl());
284 ++Start;
285 }
286
287 // Compute the static offset of the ultimate destination within its
288 // allocating subobject (the virtual base, if there is one, or else
289 // the "complete" object that we see).
290 CharUnits NonVirtualOffset = CGM.computeNonVirtualBaseClassOffset(
291 VBase ? VBase : Derived, Start, PathEnd);
292
293 // If there's a virtual step, we can sometimes "devirtualize" it.
294 // For now, that's limited to when the derived type is final.
295 // TODO: "devirtualize" this for accesses to known-complete objects.
296 if (VBase && Derived->hasAttr<FinalAttr>()) {
297 const ASTRecordLayout &layout = getContext().getASTRecordLayout(Derived);
298 CharUnits vBaseOffset = layout.getVBaseClassOffset(VBase);
299 NonVirtualOffset += vBaseOffset;
300 VBase = nullptr; // we no longer have a virtual step
301 }
302
303 // Get the base pointer type.
304 llvm::Type *BasePtrTy =
305 ConvertType((PathEnd[-1])->getType())
306 ->getPointerTo(Value.getType()->getPointerAddressSpace());
307
308 QualType DerivedTy = getContext().getRecordType(Derived);
309 CharUnits DerivedAlign = CGM.getClassPointerAlignment(Derived);
310
311 // If the static offset is zero and we don't have a virtual step,
312 // just do a bitcast; null checks are unnecessary.
313 if (NonVirtualOffset.isZero() && !VBase) {
314 if (sanitizePerformTypeCheck()) {
315 SanitizerSet SkippedChecks;
316 SkippedChecks.set(SanitizerKind::Null, !NullCheckValue);
317 EmitTypeCheck(TCK_Upcast, Loc, Value.getPointer(),
318 DerivedTy, DerivedAlign, SkippedChecks);
319 }
320 return Builder.CreateBitCast(Value, BasePtrTy);
321 }
322
323 llvm::BasicBlock *origBB = nullptr;
324 llvm::BasicBlock *endBB = nullptr;
325
326 // Skip over the offset (and the vtable load) if we're supposed to
327 // null-check the pointer.
328 if (NullCheckValue) {
329 origBB = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
330 llvm::BasicBlock *notNullBB = createBasicBlock("cast.notnull");
331 endBB = createBasicBlock("cast.end");
332
333 llvm::Value *isNull = Builder.CreateIsNull(Value.getPointer());
334 Builder.CreateCondBr(isNull, endBB, notNullBB);
335 EmitBlock(notNullBB);
336 }
337
338 if (sanitizePerformTypeCheck()) {
339 SanitizerSet SkippedChecks;
340 SkippedChecks.set(SanitizerKind::Null, true);
341 EmitTypeCheck(VBase ? TCK_UpcastToVirtualBase : TCK_Upcast, Loc,
342 Value.getPointer(), DerivedTy, DerivedAlign, SkippedChecks);
343 }
344
345 // Compute the virtual offset.
346 llvm::Value *VirtualOffset = nullptr;
347 if (VBase) {
348 VirtualOffset =
349 CGM.getCXXABI().GetVirtualBaseClassOffset(*this, Value, Derived, VBase);
350 }
351
352 // Apply both offsets.
353 Value = ApplyNonVirtualAndVirtualOffset(*this, Value, NonVirtualOffset,
354 VirtualOffset, Derived, VBase);
355
356 // Cast to the destination type.
357 Value = Builder.CreateBitCast(Value, BasePtrTy);
358
359 // Build a phi if we needed a null check.
360 if (NullCheckValue) {
361 llvm::BasicBlock *notNullBB = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
362 Builder.CreateBr(endBB);
363 EmitBlock(endBB);
364
365 llvm::PHINode *PHI = Builder.CreatePHI(BasePtrTy, 2, "cast.result");
366 PHI->addIncoming(Value.getPointer(), notNullBB);
367 PHI->addIncoming(llvm::Constant::getNullValue(BasePtrTy), origBB);
368 Value = Address(PHI, Value.getAlignment());
369 }
370
371 return Value;
372}

374Address
375CodeGenFunction::GetAddressOfDerivedClass(Address BaseAddr,
376 const CXXRecordDecl *Derived,
377 CastExpr::path_const_iterator PathBegin,
378 CastExpr::path_const_iterator PathEnd,
379 bool NullCheckValue) {
380 assert(PathBegin != PathEnd && "Base path should not be empty!");
381
382 QualType DerivedTy =
383 getContext().getCanonicalType(getContext().getTagDeclType(Derived));
384 llvm::Type *DerivedPtrTy = ConvertType(DerivedTy)->getPointerTo(
385 CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS());
386
387 llvm::Value *NonVirtualOffset =
388 CGM.GetNonVirtualBaseClassOffset(Derived, PathBegin, PathEnd);
389
390 if (!NonVirtualOffset) {
391 // No offset, we can just cast back.
392 return Builder.CreateBitCast(BaseAddr, DerivedPtrTy);
393 }
394
395 llvm::BasicBlock *CastNull = nullptr;
396 llvm::BasicBlock *CastNotNull = nullptr;
397 llvm::BasicBlock *CastEnd = nullptr;
398
399 if (NullCheckValue) {
400 CastNull = createBasicBlock("cast.null");
401 CastNotNull = createBasicBlock("cast.notnull");
402 CastEnd = createBasicBlock("cast.end");
403
404 llvm::Value *IsNull = Builder.CreateIsNull(BaseAddr.getPointer());
405 Builder.CreateCondBr(IsNull, CastNull, CastNotNull);
406 EmitBlock(CastNotNull);
407 }
408
409 // Apply the offset.
410 llvm::Value *Value = Builder.CreateBitCast(BaseAddr.getPointer(), Int8PtrTy);
411 Value = Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(Value, Builder.CreateNeg(NonVirtualOffset),
412 "sub.ptr");
413
414 // Just cast.
415 Value = Builder.CreateBitCast(Value, DerivedPtrTy);
416
417 // Produce a PHI if we had a null-check.
418 if (NullCheckValue) {
419 Builder.CreateBr(CastEnd);
420 EmitBlock(CastNull);
421 Builder.CreateBr(CastEnd);
422 EmitBlock(CastEnd);
423
424 llvm::PHINode *PHI = Builder.CreatePHI(Value->getType(), 2);
425 PHI->addIncoming(Value, CastNotNull);
426 PHI->addIncoming(llvm::Constant::getNullValue(Value->getType()), CastNull);
427 Value = PHI;
428 }
429
430 return Address(Value, CGM.getClassPointerAlignment(Derived));
431}

433llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::GetVTTParameter(GlobalDecl GD,
434 bool ForVirtualBase,
435 bool Delegating) {
436 if (!CGM.getCXXABI().NeedsVTTParameter(GD)) {
437 // This constructor/destructor does not need a VTT parameter.
438 return nullptr;
439 }
440
441 const CXXRecordDecl *RD = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(CurCodeDecl)->getParent();
442 const CXXRecordDecl *Base = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(GD.getDecl())->getParent();
443
444 llvm::Value *VTT;
445
446 uint64_t SubVTTIndex;
447
448 if (Delegating) {
449 // If this is a delegating constructor call, just load the VTT.
450 return LoadCXXVTT();
451 } else if (RD == Base) {
452 // If the record matches the base, this is the complete ctor/dtor
453 // variant calling the base variant in a class with virtual bases.
454 assert(!CGM.getCXXABI().NeedsVTTParameter(CurGD) &&
455 "doing no-op VTT offset in base dtor/ctor?");
456 assert(!ForVirtualBase && "Can't have same class as virtual base!");
457 SubVTTIndex = 0;
458 } else {
459 const ASTRecordLayout &Layout = getContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
460 CharUnits BaseOffset = ForVirtualBase ?
461 Layout.getVBaseClassOffset(Base) :
462 Layout.getBaseClassOffset(Base);
463
464 SubVTTIndex =
465 CGM.getVTables().getSubVTTIndex(RD, BaseSubobject(Base, BaseOffset));
466 assert(SubVTTIndex != 0 && "Sub-VTT index must be greater than zero!");
467 }
468
469 if (CGM.getCXXABI().NeedsVTTParameter(CurGD)) {
470 // A VTT parameter was passed to the constructor, use it.
471 VTT = LoadCXXVTT();
472 VTT = Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP1_64(VTT, SubVTTIndex);
473 } else {
474 // We're the complete constructor, so get the VTT by name.
475 VTT = CGM.getVTables().GetAddrOfVTT(RD);
476 VTT = Builder.CreateConstInBoundsGEP2_64(VTT, 0, SubVTTIndex);
477 }
478
479 return VTT;
480}

482namespace {
483 /// Call the destructor for a direct base class.
484 struct CallBaseDtor final : EHScopeStack::Cleanup {
485 const CXXRecordDecl *BaseClass;
486 bool BaseIsVirtual;
487 CallBaseDtor(const CXXRecordDecl *Base, bool BaseIsVirtual)
488 : BaseClass(Base), BaseIsVirtual(BaseIsVirtual) {}
489
490 void Emit(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Flags flags) override {
491 const CXXRecordDecl *DerivedClass =
492 cast<CXXMethodDecl>(CGF.CurCodeDecl)->getParent();
493
494 const CXXDestructorDecl *D = BaseClass->getDestructor();
495 Address Addr =
496 CGF.GetAddressOfDirectBaseInCompleteClass(CGF.LoadCXXThisAddress(),
497 DerivedClass, BaseClass,
498 BaseIsVirtual);
499 CGF.EmitCXXDestructorCall(D, Dtor_Base, BaseIsVirtual,
500 /*Delegating=*/false, Addr);
501 }
502 };
503
504 /// A visitor which checks whether an initializer uses 'this' in a
505 /// way which requires the vtable to be properly set.
506 struct DynamicThisUseChecker : ConstEvaluatedExprVisitor<DynamicThisUseChecker> {
507 typedef ConstEvaluatedExprVisitor<DynamicThisUseChecker> super;
508
509 bool UsesThis;
510
511 DynamicThisUseChecker(const ASTContext &C) : super(C), UsesThis(false) {}
512
513 // Black-list all explicit and implicit references to 'this'.
514 //
515 // Do we need to worry about external references to 'this' derived
516 // from arbitrary code? If so, then anything which runs arbitrary
517 // external code might potentially access the vtable.
518 void VisitCXXThisExpr(const CXXThisExpr *E) { UsesThis = true; }
519 };
520} // end anonymous namespace
521
522static bool BaseInitializerUsesThis(ASTContext &C, const Expr *Init) {
523 DynamicThisUseChecker Checker(C);
524 Checker.Visit(Init);
525 return Checker.UsesThis;
526}

528static void EmitBaseInitializer(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
529 const CXXRecordDecl *ClassDecl,
530 CXXCtorInitializer *BaseInit) {
531 assert(BaseInit->isBaseInitializer() &&
532 "Must have base initializer!");
533
534 Address ThisPtr = CGF.LoadCXXThisAddress();
535
536 const Type *BaseType = BaseInit->getBaseClass();
537 CXXRecordDecl *BaseClassDecl =
538 cast<CXXRecordDecl>(BaseType->getAs<RecordType>()->getDecl());
539
540 bool isBaseVirtual = BaseInit->isBaseVirtual();
541
542 // If the initializer for the base (other than the constructor
543 // itself) accesses 'this' in any way, we need to initialize the
544 // vtables.
545 if (BaseInitializerUsesThis(CGF.getContext(), BaseInit->getInit()))
546 CGF.InitializeVTablePointers(ClassDecl);
547
548 // We can pretend to be a complete class because it only matters for
549 // virtual bases, and we only do virtual bases for complete ctors.
550 Address V =
551 CGF.GetAddressOfDirectBaseInCompleteClass(ThisPtr, ClassDecl,
552 BaseClassDecl,
553 isBaseVirtual);
554 AggValueSlot AggSlot =
555 AggValueSlot::forAddr(
556 V, Qualifiers(),
557 AggValueSlot::IsDestructed,
558 AggValueSlot::DoesNotNeedGCBarriers,
559 AggValueSlot::IsNotAliased,
560 CGF.overlapForBaseInit(ClassDecl, BaseClassDecl, isBaseVirtual));
561
562 CGF.EmitAggExpr(BaseInit->getInit(), AggSlot);
563
564 if (CGF.CGM.getLangOpts().Exceptions &&
565 !BaseClassDecl->hasTrivialDestructor())
566 CGF.EHStack.pushCleanup<CallBaseDtor>(EHCleanup, BaseClassDecl,
567 isBaseVirtual);
568}

570static bool isMemcpyEquivalentSpecialMember(const CXXMethodDecl *D) {
571 auto *CD = dyn_cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(D);
572 if (!(CD && CD->isCopyOrMoveConstructor()) &&
573 !D->isCopyAssignmentOperator() && !D->isMoveAssignmentOperator())
574 return false;
575
576 // We can emit a memcpy for a trivial copy or move constructor/assignment.
577 if (D->isTrivial() && !D->getParent()->mayInsertExtraPadding())
578 return true;
579
580 // We *must* emit a memcpy for a defaulted union copy or move op.
581 if (D->getParent()->isUnion() && D->isDefaulted())
582 return true;
583
584 return false;
585}

587static void EmitLValueForAnyFieldInitialization(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
588 CXXCtorInitializer *MemberInit,
589 LValue &LHS) {
590 FieldDecl *Field = MemberInit->getAnyMember();
591 if (MemberInit->isIndirectMemberInitializer()) {
592 // If we are initializing an anonymous union field, drill down to the field.
593 IndirectFieldDecl *IndirectField = MemberInit->getIndirectMember();
594 for (const auto *I : IndirectField->chain())
595 LHS = CGF.EmitLValueForFieldInitialization(LHS, cast<FieldDecl>(I));
596 } else {
597 LHS = CGF.EmitLValueForFieldInitialization(LHS, Field);
598 }
599}
600
601static void EmitMemberInitializer(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
602 const CXXRecordDecl *ClassDecl,
603 CXXCtorInitializer *MemberInit,
604 const CXXConstructorDecl *Constructor,
605 FunctionArgList &Args) {
606 ApplyDebugLocation Loc(CGF, MemberInit->getSourceLocation());
607 assert(MemberInit->isAnyMemberInitializer() &&
608 "Must have member initializer!");
609 assert(MemberInit->getInit() && "Must have initializer!");
610
611 // non-static data member initializers.
612 FieldDecl *Field = MemberInit->getAnyMember();
613 QualType FieldType = Field->getType();
614
615 llvm::Value *ThisPtr = CGF.LoadCXXThis();
616 QualType RecordTy = CGF.getContext().getTypeDeclType(ClassDecl);
617 LValue LHS;
618
619 // If a base constructor is being emitted, create an LValue that has the
620 // non-virtual alignment.
621 if (CGF.CurGD.getCtorType() == Ctor_Base)
622 LHS = CGF.MakeNaturalAlignPointeeAddrLValue(ThisPtr, RecordTy);
623 else
624 LHS = CGF.MakeNaturalAlignAddrLValue(ThisPtr, RecordTy);
625
626 EmitLValueForAnyFieldInitialization(CGF, MemberInit, LHS);
627
628 // Special case: if we are in a copy or move constructor, and we are copying
629 // an array of PODs or classes with trivial copy constructors, ignore the
630 // AST and perform the copy we know is equivalent.
631 // FIXME: This is hacky at best... if we had a bit more explicit information
632 // in the AST, we could generalize it more easily.
633 const ConstantArrayType *Array
634 = CGF.getContext().getAsConstantArrayType(FieldType);
635 if (Array && Constructor->isDefaulted() &&
636 Constructor->isCopyOrMoveConstructor()) {
637 QualType BaseElementTy = CGF.getContext().getBaseElementType(Array);
638 CXXConstructExpr *CE = dyn_cast<CXXConstructExpr>(MemberInit->getInit());
639 if (BaseElementTy.isPODType(CGF.getContext()) ||
640 (CE && isMemcpyEquivalentSpecialMember(CE->getConstructor()))) {
641 unsigned SrcArgIndex =
642 CGF.CGM.getCXXABI().getSrcArgforCopyCtor(Constructor, Args);
643 llvm::Value *SrcPtr
644 = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(CGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(Args[SrcArgIndex]));
645 LValue ThisRHSLV = CGF.MakeNaturalAlignAddrLValue(SrcPtr, RecordTy);
646 LValue Src = CGF.EmitLValueForFieldInitialization(ThisRHSLV, Field);
647
648 // Copy the aggregate.
649 CGF.EmitAggregateCopy(LHS, Src, FieldType, CGF.overlapForFieldInit(Field),
650 LHS.isVolatileQualified());
651 // Ensure that we destroy the objects if an exception is thrown later in
652 // the constructor.
653 QualType::DestructionKind dtorKind = FieldType.isDestructedType();
654 if (CGF.needsEHCleanup(dtorKind))
655 CGF.pushEHDestroy(dtorKind, LHS.getAddress(), FieldType);
656 return;
657 }
658 }
659
660 CGF.EmitInitializerForField(Field, LHS, MemberInit->getInit());
661}
662
663void CodeGenFunction::EmitInitializerForField(FieldDecl *Field, LValue LHS,
664 Expr *Init) {
665 QualType FieldType = Field->getType();
666 switch (getEvaluationKind(FieldType)) {
667 case TEK_Scalar:
668 if (LHS.isSimple()) {
669 EmitExprAsInit(Init, Field, LHS, false);
670 } else {
671 RValue RHS = RValue::get(EmitScalarExpr(Init));
672 EmitStoreThroughLValue(RHS, LHS);
673 }
674 break;
675 case TEK_Complex:
676 EmitComplexExprIntoLValue(Init, LHS, /*isInit*/ true);
677 break;
678 case TEK_Aggregate: {
679 AggValueSlot Slot =
680 AggValueSlot::forLValue(
681 LHS,
682 AggValueSlot::IsDestructed,
683 AggValueSlot::DoesNotNeedGCBarriers,
684 AggValueSlot::IsNotAliased,
685 overlapForFieldInit(Field),
686 AggValueSlot::IsNotZeroed,
687 // Checks are made by the code that calls constructor.
688 AggValueSlot::IsSanitizerChecked);
689 EmitAggExpr(Init, Slot);
690 break;
691 }
692 }
693
694 // Ensure that we destroy this object if an exception is thrown
695 // later in the constructor.
696 QualType::DestructionKind dtorKind = FieldType.isDestructedType();
697 if (needsEHCleanup(dtorKind))
698 pushEHDestroy(dtorKind, LHS.getAddress(), FieldType);
699}
700
701/// Checks whether the given constructor is a valid subject for the
702/// complete-to-base constructor delegation optimization, i.e.
703/// emitting the complete constructor as a simple call to the base
704/// constructor.
705bool CodeGenFunction::IsConstructorDelegationValid(
706 const CXXConstructorDecl *Ctor) {
707
708 // Currently we disable the optimization for classes with virtual
709 // bases because (1) the addresses of parameter variables need to be
710 // consistent across all initializers but (2) the delegate function
711 // call necessarily creates a second copy of the parameter variable.
712 //
713 // The limiting example (purely theoretical AFAIK):
714 // struct A { A(int &c) { c++; } };
715 // struct B : virtual A {
716 // B(int count) : A(count) { printf("%d\n", count); }
717 // };
718 // ...although even this example could in principle be emitted as a
719 // delegation since the address of the parameter doesn't escape.
720 if (Ctor->getParent()->getNumVBases()) {
721 // TODO: white-list trivial vbase initializers. This case wouldn't
722 // be subject to the restrictions below.
723
724 // TODO: white-list cases where:
725 // - there are no non-reference parameters to the constructor
726 // - the initializers don't access any non-reference parameters
727 // - the initializers don't take the address of non-reference
728 // parameters
729 // - etc.
730 // If we ever add any of the above cases, remember that:
731 // - function-try-blocks will always blacklist this optimization
732 // - we need to perform the constructor prologue and cleanup in
733 // EmitConstructorBody.
734
735 return false;
736 }
737
738 // We also disable the optimization for variadic functions because
739 // it's impossible to "re-pass" varargs.
740 if (Ctor->getType()->getAs<FunctionProtoType>()->isVariadic())
741 return false;
742
743 // FIXME: Decide if we can do a delegation of a delegating constructor.
744 if (Ctor->isDelegatingConstructor())
745 return false;
746
747 return true;
748}
749
750// Emit code in ctor (Prologue==true) or dtor (Prologue==false)
751// to poison the extra field paddings inserted under
752// -fsanitize-address-field-padding=1|2.
753void CodeGenFunction::EmitAsanPrologueOrEpilogue(bool Prologue) {
754 ASTContext &Context = getContext();
755 const CXXRecordDecl *ClassDecl =
756 Prologue ? cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(CurGD.getDecl())->getParent()
757 : cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(CurGD.getDecl())->getParent();
758 if (!ClassDecl->mayInsertExtraPadding()) return;
759
760 struct SizeAndOffset {
761 uint64_t Size;
762 uint64_t Offset;
763 };
764
765 unsigned PtrSize = CGM.getDataLayout().getPointerSizeInBits(
766 CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS());
767 const ASTRecordLayout &Info = Context.getASTRecordLayout(ClassDecl);
768
769 // Populate sizes and offsets of fields.
770 SmallVector<SizeAndOffset, 16> SSV(Info.getFieldCount());
771 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Info.getFieldCount(); i != e; ++i)
772 SSV[i].Offset =
773 Context.toCharUnitsFromBits(Info.getFieldOffset(i)).getQuantity();
774
775 size_t NumFields = 0;
776 for (const auto *Field : ClassDecl->fields()) {
777 const FieldDecl *D = Field;
778 std::pair<CharUnits, CharUnits> FieldInfo =
779 Context.getTypeInfoInChars(D->getType());
780 CharUnits FieldSize = FieldInfo.first;
781 assert(NumFields < SSV.size());
782 SSV[NumFields].Size = D->isBitField() ? 0 : FieldSize.getQuantity();
783 NumFields++;
784 }
785 assert(NumFields == SSV.size());
786 if (SSV.size() <= 1) return;
787
788 // We will insert calls to __asan_* run-time functions.
789 // LLVM AddressSanitizer pass may decide to inline them later.
790 llvm::Type *Args[2] = {IntPtrTy, IntPtrTy};
791 llvm::FunctionType *FTy =
792 llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.VoidTy, Args, false);
793 llvm::FunctionCallee F = CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(
794 FTy, Prologue ? "__asan_poison_intra_object_redzone"
795 : "__asan_unpoison_intra_object_redzone");
796
797 llvm::Value *ThisPtr = LoadCXXThis();
798 ThisPtr = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(ThisPtr, IntPtrTy);
799 uint64_t TypeSize = Info.getNonVirtualSize().getQuantity();
800 // For each field check if it has sufficient padding,
801 // if so (un)poison it with a call.
802 for (size_t i = 0; i < SSV.size(); i++) {
803 uint64_t AsanAlignment = 8;
804 uint64_t NextField = i == SSV.size() - 1 ? TypeSize : SSV[i + 1].Offset;
805 uint64_t PoisonSize = NextField - SSV[i].Offset - SSV[i].Size;
806 uint64_t EndOffset = SSV[i].Offset + SSV[i].Size;
807 if (PoisonSize < AsanAlignment || !SSV[i].Size ||
808 (NextField % AsanAlignment) != 0)
809 continue;
810 Builder.CreateCall(
811 F, {Builder.CreateAdd(ThisPtr, Builder.getIntN(PtrSize, EndOffset)),
812 Builder.getIntN(PtrSize, PoisonSize)});
813 }
814}
815
816/// EmitConstructorBody - Emits the body of the current constructor.
817void CodeGenFunction::EmitConstructorBody(FunctionArgList &Args) {
818 EmitAsanPrologueOrEpilogue(true);
819 const CXXConstructorDecl *Ctor = cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(CurGD.getDecl());
820 CXXCtorType CtorType = CurGD.getCtorType();
821
822 assert((CGM.getTarget().getCXXABI().hasConstructorVariants() ||
823 CtorType == Ctor_Complete) &&
824 "can only generate complete ctor for this ABI");
825
826 // Before we go any further, try the complete->base constructor
827 // delegation optimization.
828 if (CtorType == Ctor_Complete && IsConstructorDelegationValid(Ctor) &&
829 CGM.getTarget().getCXXABI().hasConstructorVariants()) {
830 EmitDelegateCXXConstructorCall(Ctor, Ctor_Base, Args, Ctor->getEndLoc());
831 return;
832 }
833
834 const FunctionDecl *Definition = nullptr;
835 Stmt *Body = Ctor->getBody(Definition);
836 assert(Definition == Ctor && "emitting wrong constructor body");
837
838 // Enter the function-try-block before the constructor prologue if
839 // applicable.
840 bool IsTryBody = (Body && isa<CXXTryStmt>(Body));
841 if (IsTryBody)
842 EnterCXXTryStmt(*cast<CXXTryStmt>(Body), true);
843
844 incrementProfileCounter(Body);
845
846 RunCleanupsScope RunCleanups(*this);
847
848 // TODO: in restricted cases, we can emit the vbase initializers of
849 // a complete ctor and then delegate to the base ctor.
850
851 // Emit the constructor prologue, i.e. the base and member
852 // initializers.
853 EmitCtorPrologue(Ctor, CtorType, Args);
854
855 // Emit the body of the statement.
856 if (IsTryBody)
857 EmitStmt(cast<CXXTryStmt>(Body)->getTryBlock());
858 else if (Body)
859 EmitStmt(Body);
860
861 // Emit any cleanup blocks associated with the member or base
862 // initializers, which includes (along the exceptional path) the
863 // destructors for those members and bases that were fully
864 // constructed.
865 RunCleanups.ForceCleanup();
866
867 if (IsTryBody)
868 ExitCXXTryStmt(*cast<CXXTryStmt>(Body), true);
869}

892namespace {
893 class FieldMemcpyizer {
894 public:
895 FieldMemcpyizer(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const CXXRecordDecl *ClassDecl,
896 const VarDecl *SrcRec)
897 : CGF(CGF), ClassDecl(ClassDecl), SrcRec(SrcRec),
898 RecLayout(CGF.getContext().getASTRecordLayout(ClassDecl)),
899 FirstField(nullptr), LastField(nullptr), FirstFieldOffset(0),
900 LastFieldOffset(0), LastAddedFieldIndex(0) {}
901
902 bool isMemcpyableField(FieldDecl *F) const {
903 // Never memcpy fields when we are adding poisoned paddings.
904 if (CGF.getContext().getLangOpts().SanitizeAddressFieldPadding)
905 return false;
906 Qualifiers Qual = F->getType().getQualifiers();
907 if (Qual.hasVolatile() || Qual.hasObjCLifetime())
908 return false;
909 return true;
910 }
911
912 void addMemcpyableField(FieldDecl *F) {
913 if (!FirstField)
914 addInitialField(F);
915 else
916 addNextField(F);
917 }
918
919 CharUnits getMemcpySize(uint64_t FirstByteOffset) const {
920 ASTContext &Ctx = CGF.getContext();
921 unsigned LastFieldSize =
922 LastField->isBitField()
923 ? LastField->getBitWidthValue(Ctx)
924 : Ctx.toBits(
925 Ctx.getTypeInfoDataSizeInChars(LastField->getType()).first);
926 uint64_t MemcpySizeBits = LastFieldOffset + LastFieldSize -
927 FirstByteOffset + Ctx.getCharWidth() - 1;
928 CharUnits MemcpySize = Ctx.toCharUnitsFromBits(MemcpySizeBits);
929 return MemcpySize;
930 }
931
932 void emitMemcpy() {
933 // Give the subclass a chance to bail out if it feels the memcpy isn't
934 // worth it (e.g. Hasn't aggregated enough data).
935 if (!FirstField) {
936 return;
937 }
938
939 uint64_t FirstByteOffset;
940 if (FirstField->isBitField()) {
941 const CGRecordLayout &RL =
942 CGF.getTypes().getCGRecordLayout(FirstField->getParent());
943 const CGBitFieldInfo &BFInfo = RL.getBitFieldInfo(FirstField);
944 // FirstFieldOffset is not appropriate for bitfields,
945 // we need to use the storage offset instead.
946 FirstByteOffset = CGF.getContext().toBits(BFInfo.StorageOffset);
947 } else {
948 FirstByteOffset = FirstFieldOffset;
949 }
950
951 CharUnits MemcpySize = getMemcpySize(FirstByteOffset);
952 QualType RecordTy = CGF.getContext().getTypeDeclType(ClassDecl);
953 Address ThisPtr = CGF.LoadCXXThisAddress();
954 LValue DestLV = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(ThisPtr, RecordTy);
955 LValue Dest = CGF.EmitLValueForFieldInitialization(DestLV, FirstField);
956 llvm::Value *SrcPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(CGF.GetAddrOfLocalVar(SrcRec));
957 LValue SrcLV = CGF.MakeNaturalAlignAddrLValue(SrcPtr, RecordTy);
958 LValue Src = CGF.EmitLValueForFieldInitialization(SrcLV, FirstField);
959
960 emitMemcpyIR(Dest.isBitField() ? Dest.getBitFieldAddress() : Dest.getAddress(),
961 Src.isBitField() ? Src.getBitFieldAddress() : Src.getAddress(),
962 MemcpySize);
963 reset();
964 }
965
966 void reset() {
967 FirstField = nullptr;
968 }
969
970 protected:
971 CodeGenFunction &CGF;
972 const CXXRecordDecl *ClassDecl;
973
974 private:
975 void emitMemcpyIR(Address DestPtr, Address SrcPtr, CharUnits Size) {
976 llvm::PointerType *DPT = DestPtr.getType();
977 llvm::Type *DBP =
978 llvm::Type::getInt8PtrTy(CGF.getLLVMContext(), DPT->getAddressSpace());
979 DestPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(DestPtr, DBP);
980
981 llvm::PointerType *SPT = SrcPtr.getType();
982 llvm::Type *SBP =
983 llvm::Type::getInt8PtrTy(CGF.getLLVMContext(), SPT->getAddressSpace());
984 SrcPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(SrcPtr, SBP);
985
986 CGF.Builder.CreateMemCpy(DestPtr, SrcPtr, Size.getQuantity());
987 }
988
989 void addInitialField(FieldDecl *F) {
990 FirstField = F;
991 LastField = F;
992 FirstFieldOffset = RecLayout.getFieldOffset(F->getFieldIndex());
993 LastFieldOffset = FirstFieldOffset;
994 LastAddedFieldIndex = F->getFieldIndex();
995 }
996
997 void addNextField(FieldDecl *F) {
998 // For the most part, the following invariant will hold:
999 // F->getFieldIndex() == LastAddedFieldIndex + 1
1000 // The one exception is that Sema won't add a copy-initializer for an
1001 // unnamed bitfield, which will show up here as a gap in the sequence.
1002 assert(F->getFieldIndex() >= LastAddedFieldIndex + 1 &&
1003 "Cannot aggregate fields out of order.");
1004 LastAddedFieldIndex = F->getFieldIndex();
1005
1006 // The 'first' and 'last' fields are chosen by offset, rather than field
1007 // index. This allows the code to support bitfields, as well as regular
1008 // fields.
1009 uint64_t FOffset = RecLayout.getFieldOffset(F->getFieldIndex());
1010 if (FOffset < FirstFieldOffset) {
1011 FirstField = F;
1012 FirstFieldOffset = FOffset;
1013 } else if (FOffset >= LastFieldOffset) {
1014 LastField = F;
1015 LastFieldOffset = FOffset;
1016 }
1017 }
1018
1019 const VarDecl *SrcRec;
1020 const ASTRecordLayout &RecLayout;
1021 FieldDecl *FirstField;
1022 FieldDecl *LastField;
1023 uint64_t FirstFieldOffset, LastFieldOffset;
1024 unsigned LastAddedFieldIndex;
1025 };
1026
1027 class ConstructorMemcpyizer : public FieldMemcpyizer {
1028 private:
1029 /// Get source argument for copy constructor. Returns null if not a copy
1030 /// constructor.
1031 static const VarDecl *getTrivialCopySource(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1032 const CXXConstructorDecl *CD,
1033 FunctionArgList &Args) {
1034 if (CD->isCopyOrMoveConstructor() && CD->isDefaulted())
1035 return Args[CGF.CGM.getCXXABI().getSrcArgforCopyCtor(CD, Args)];
1036 return nullptr;
1037 }
1038
1039 // Returns true if a CXXCtorInitializer represents a member initialization
1040 // that can be rolled into a memcpy.
1041 bool isMemberInitMemcpyable(CXXCtorInitializer *MemberInit) const {
1042 if (!MemcpyableCtor)
1043 return false;
1044 FieldDecl *Field = MemberInit->getMember();
1045 assert(Field && "No field for member init.");
1046 QualType FieldType = Field->getType();
1047 CXXConstructExpr *CE = dyn_cast<CXXConstructExpr>(MemberInit->getInit());
1048
1049 // Bail out on non-memcpyable, not-trivially-copyable members.
1050 if (!(CE && isMemcpyEquivalentSpecialMember(CE->getConstructor())) &&
1051 !(FieldType.isTriviallyCopyableType(CGF.getContext()) ||
1052 FieldType->isReferenceType()))
1053 return false;
1054
1055 // Bail out on volatile fields.
1056 if (!isMemcpyableField(Field))
1057 return false;
1058
1059 // Otherwise we're good.
1060 return true;
1061 }
1062
1063 public:
1064 ConstructorMemcpyizer(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const CXXConstructorDecl *CD,
1065 FunctionArgList &Args)
1066 : FieldMemcpyizer(CGF, CD->getParent(), getTrivialCopySource(CGF, CD, Args)),
1067 ConstructorDecl(CD),
1068 MemcpyableCtor(CD->isDefaulted() &&
1069 CD->isCopyOrMoveConstructor() &&
1070 CGF.getLangOpts().getGC() == LangOptions::NonGC),
1071 Args(Args) { }
1072
1073 void addMemberInitializer(CXXCtorInitializer *MemberInit) {
1074 if (isMemberInitMemcpyable(MemberInit)) {
1075 AggregatedInits.push_back(MemberInit);
1076 addMemcpyableField(MemberInit->getMember());
1077 } else {
1078 emitAggregatedInits();
1079 EmitMemberInitializer(CGF, ConstructorDecl->getParent(), MemberInit,
1080 ConstructorDecl, Args);
1081 }
1082 }
1083
1084 void emitAggregatedInits() {
1085 if (AggregatedInits.size() <= 1) {
1086 // This memcpy is too small to be worthwhile. Fall back on default
1087 // codegen.
1088 if (!AggregatedInits.empty()) {
1089 CopyingValueRepresentation CVR(CGF);
1090 EmitMemberInitializer(CGF, ConstructorDecl->getParent(),
1091 AggregatedInits[0], ConstructorDecl, Args);
1092 AggregatedInits.clear();
1093 }
1094 reset();
1095 return;
1096 }
1097
1098 pushEHDestructors();
1099 emitMemcpy();
1100 AggregatedInits.clear();
1101 }
1102
1103 void pushEHDestructors() {
1104 Address ThisPtr = CGF.LoadCXXThisAddress();
1105 QualType RecordTy = CGF.getContext().getTypeDeclType(ClassDecl);
1106 LValue LHS = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(ThisPtr, RecordTy);
1107
1108 for (unsigned i = 0; i < AggregatedInits.size(); ++i) {
1109 CXXCtorInitializer *MemberInit = AggregatedInits[i];
1110 QualType FieldType = MemberInit->getAnyMember()->getType();
1111 QualType::DestructionKind dtorKind = FieldType.isDestructedType();
1112 if (!CGF.needsEHCleanup(dtorKind))
1113 continue;
1114 LValue FieldLHS = LHS;
1115 EmitLValueForAnyFieldInitialization(CGF, MemberInit, FieldLHS);
1116 CGF.pushEHDestroy(dtorKind, FieldLHS.getAddress(), FieldType);
1117 }
1118 }
1119
1120 void finish() {
1121 emitAggregatedInits();
1122 }
1123
1124 private:
1125 const CXXConstructorDecl *ConstructorDecl;
1126 bool MemcpyableCtor;
1127 FunctionArgList &Args;
1128 SmallVector<CXXCtorInitializer*, 16> AggregatedInits;
1129 };
1130
1131 class AssignmentMemcpyizer : public FieldMemcpyizer {
1132 private:
1133 // Returns the memcpyable field copied by the given statement, if one
1134 // exists. Otherwise returns null.
1135 FieldDecl *getMemcpyableField(Stmt *S) {
1136 if (!AssignmentsMemcpyable)
1137 return nullptr;
1138 if (BinaryOperator *BO = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(S)) {
1139 // Recognise trivial assignments.
1140 if (BO->getOpcode() != BO_Assign)
1141 return nullptr;
1142 MemberExpr *ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(BO->getLHS());
1143 if (!ME)
1144 return nullptr;
1145 FieldDecl *Field = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(ME->getMemberDecl());
1146 if (!Field || !isMemcpyableField(Field))
1147 return nullptr;
1148 Stmt *RHS = BO->getRHS();
1149 if (ImplicitCastExpr *EC = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(RHS))
1150 RHS = EC->getSubExpr();
1151 if (!RHS)
1152 return nullptr;
1153 if (MemberExpr *ME2 = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(RHS)) {
1154 if (ME2->getMemberDecl() == Field)
1155 return Field;
1156 }
1157 return nullptr;
1158 } else if (CXXMemberCallExpr *MCE = dyn_cast<CXXMemberCallExpr>(S)) {
1159 CXXMethodDecl *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(MCE->getCalleeDecl());
1160 if (!(MD && isMemcpyEquivalentSpecialMember(MD)))
1161 return nullptr;
1162 MemberExpr *IOA = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(MCE->getImplicitObjectArgument());
1163 if (!IOA)
1164 return nullptr;
1165 FieldDecl *Field = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(IOA->getMemberDecl());
1166 if (!Field || !isMemcpyableField(Field))
1167 return nullptr;
1168 MemberExpr *Arg0 = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(MCE->getArg(0));
1169 if (!Arg0 || Field != dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(Arg0->getMemberDecl()))
1170 return nullptr;
1171 return Field;
1172 } else if (CallExpr *CE = dyn_cast<CallExpr>(S)) {
1173 FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(CE->getCalleeDecl());
1174 if (!FD || FD->getBuiltinID() != Builtin::BI__builtin_memcpy)
1175 return nullptr;
1176 Expr *DstPtr = CE->getArg(0);
1177 if (ImplicitCastExpr *DC = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(DstPtr))
1178 DstPtr = DC->getSubExpr();
1179 UnaryOperator *DUO = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(DstPtr);
1180 if (!DUO || DUO->getOpcode() != UO_AddrOf)
1181 return nullptr;
1182 MemberExpr *ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(DUO->getSubExpr());
1183 if (!ME)
1184 return nullptr;
1185 FieldDecl *Field = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(ME->getMemberDecl());
1186 if (!Field || !isMemcpyableField(Field))
1187 return nullptr;
1188 Expr *SrcPtr = CE->getArg(1);
1189 if (ImplicitCastExpr *SC = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(SrcPtr))
1190 SrcPtr = SC->getSubExpr();
1191 UnaryOperator *SUO = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(SrcPtr);
1192 if (!SUO || SUO->getOpcode() != UO_AddrOf)
1193 return nullptr;
1194 MemberExpr *ME2 = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(SUO->getSubExpr());
1195 if (!ME2 || Field != dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(ME2->getMemberDecl()))
1196 return nullptr;
1197 return Field;
1198 }
1199
1200 return nullptr;
1201 }
1202
1203 bool AssignmentsMemcpyable;
1204 SmallVector<Stmt*, 16> AggregatedStmts;
1205
1206 public:
1207 AssignmentMemcpyizer(CodeGenFunction &CGF, const CXXMethodDecl *AD,
1208 FunctionArgList &Args)
1209 : FieldMemcpyizer(CGF, AD->getParent(), Args[Args.size() - 1]),
1210 AssignmentsMemcpyable(CGF.getLangOpts().getGC() == LangOptions::NonGC) {
1211 assert(Args.size() == 2);
1212 }
1213
1214 void emitAssignment(Stmt *S) {
1215 FieldDecl *F = getMemcpyableField(S);
1216 if (F) {
1217 addMemcpyableField(F);
1218 AggregatedStmts.push_back(S);
1219 } else {
1220 emitAggregatedStmts();
1221 CGF.EmitStmt(S);
1222 }
1223 }
1224
1225 void emitAggregatedStmts() {
1226 if (AggregatedStmts.size() <= 1) {
1227 if (!AggregatedStmts.empty()) {
1228 CopyingValueRepresentation CVR(CGF);
1229 CGF.EmitStmt(AggregatedStmts[0]);
1230 }
1231 reset();
1232 }
1233
1234 emitMemcpy();
1235 AggregatedStmts.clear();
1236 }
1237
1238 void finish() {
1239 emitAggregatedStmts();
1240 }
1241 };
1242} // end anonymous namespace

1244static bool isInitializerOfDynamicClass(const CXXCtorInitializer *BaseInit) {
1245 const Type *BaseType = BaseInit->getBaseClass();
1246 const auto *BaseClassDecl =
1247 cast<CXXRecordDecl>(BaseType->getAs<RecordType>()->getDecl());
1248 return BaseClassDecl->isDynamicClass();

1250
1251/// EmitCtorPrologue - This routine generates necessary code to initialize
1252/// base classes and non-static data members belonging to this constructor.
1253void CodeGenFunction::EmitCtorPrologue(const CXXConstructorDecl *CD,
1254 CXXCtorType CtorType,
1255 FunctionArgList &Args) {
1256 if (CD->isDelegatingConstructor())
1257 return EmitDelegatingCXXConstructorCall(CD, Args);
1258
1259 const CXXRecordDecl *ClassDecl = CD->getParent();
1260
1261 CXXConstructorDecl::init_const_iterator B = CD->init_begin(),
1262 E = CD->init_end();
1263
1264 // Virtual base initializers first, if any. They aren't needed if:
1265 // - This is a base ctor variant
1266 // - There are no vbases
1267 // - The class is abstract, so a complete object of it cannot be constructed
1268 //
1269 // The check for an abstract class is necessary because sema may not have
1270 // marked virtual base destructors referenced.
1271 bool ConstructVBases = CtorType != Ctor_Base &&
1272 ClassDecl->getNumVBases() != 0 &&
1273 !ClassDecl->isAbstract();
1274
1275 // In the Microsoft C++ ABI, there are no constructor variants. Instead, the
1276 // constructor of a class with virtual bases takes an additional parameter to
1277 // conditionally construct the virtual bases. Emit that check here.
1278 llvm::BasicBlock *BaseCtorContinueBB = nullptr;
1279 if (ConstructVBases &&
1280 !CGM.getTarget().getCXXABI().hasConstructorVariants()) {
1281 BaseCtorContinueBB =
1282 CGM.getCXXABI().EmitCtorCompleteObjectHandler(*this, ClassDecl);
1283 assert(BaseCtorContinueBB);
1284 }
1285
1286 llvm::Value *const OldThis = CXXThisValue;
1287 for (; B != E && (*B)->isBaseInitializer() && (*B)->isBaseVirtual(); B++) {
1288 if (!ConstructVBases)
1289 continue;
1290 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().StrictVTablePointers &&
1291 CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel > 0 &&
1292 isInitializerOfDynamicClass(*B))
1293 CXXThisValue = Builder.CreateLaunderInvariantGroup(LoadCXXThis());
1294 EmitBaseInitializer(*this, ClassDecl, *B);
1295 }
1296
1297 if (BaseCtorContinueBB) {
1298 // Complete object handler should continue to the remaining initializers.
1299 Builder.CreateBr(BaseCtorContinueBB);
1300 EmitBlock(BaseCtorContinueBB);
1301 }
1302
1303 // Then, non-virtual base initializers.
1304 for (; B != E && (*B)->isBaseInitializer(); B++) {
1305 assert(!(*B)->isBaseVirtual());
1306
1307 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().StrictVTablePointers &&
1308 CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel > 0 &&
1309 isInitializerOfDynamicClass(*B))
1310 CXXThisValue = Builder.CreateLaunderInvariantGroup(LoadCXXThis());
1311 EmitBaseInitializer(*this, ClassDecl, *B);
1312 }
1313
1314 CXXThisValue = OldThis;
1315
1316 InitializeVTablePointers(ClassDecl);
1317
1318 // And finally, initialize class members.
1319 FieldConstructionScope FCS(*this, LoadCXXThisAddress());
1320 ConstructorMemcpyizer CM(*this, CD, Args);
1321 for (; B != E; B++) {
1322 CXXCtorInitializer *Member = (*B);
1323 assert(!Member->isBaseInitializer());
1324 assert(Member->isAnyMemberInitializer() &&
1325 "Delegating initializer on non-delegating constructor");
1326 CM.addMemberInitializer(Member);
1327 }
1328 CM.finish();
1329}
1330
1331static bool
1332FieldHasTrivialDestructorBody(ASTContext &Context, const FieldDecl *Field);
1333
1334static bool
1335HasTrivialDestructorBody(ASTContext &Context,
1336 const CXXRecordDecl *BaseClassDecl,
1337 const CXXRecordDecl *MostDerivedClassDecl)
1338{
1339 // If the destructor is trivial we don't have to check anything else.
1340 if (BaseClassDecl->hasTrivialDestructor())
1341 return true;
1342
1343 if (!BaseClassDecl->getDestructor()->hasTrivialBody())
1344 return false;
1345
1346 // Check fields.
1347 for (const auto *Field : BaseClassDecl->fields())
1348 if (!FieldHasTrivialDestructorBody(Context, Field))
1349 return false;
1350
1351 // Check non-virtual bases.
1352 for (const auto &I : BaseClassDecl->bases()) {
1353 if (I.isVirtual())
1354 continue;
1355
1356 const CXXRecordDecl *NonVirtualBase =
1357 cast<CXXRecordDecl>(I.getType()->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl());
1358 if (!HasTrivialDestructorBody(Context, NonVirtualBase,
1359 MostDerivedClassDecl))
1360 return false;
1361 }
1362
1363 if (BaseClassDecl == MostDerivedClassDecl) {
1364 // Check virtual bases.
1365 for (const auto &I : BaseClassDecl->vbases()) {
1366 const CXXRecordDecl *VirtualBase =
1367 cast<CXXRecordDecl>(I.getType()->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl());
1368 if (!HasTrivialDestructorBody(Context, VirtualBase,
1369 MostDerivedClassDecl))
1370 return false;
1371 }
1372 }
1373
1374 return true;
1375}
1376
1377static bool
1378FieldHasTrivialDestructorBody(ASTContext &Context,
1379 const FieldDecl *Field)
1380{
1381 QualType FieldBaseElementType = Context.getBaseElementType(Field->getType());
1382
1383 const RecordType *RT = FieldBaseElementType->getAs<RecordType>();
1384 if (!RT)
1385 return true;
1386
1387 CXXRecordDecl *FieldClassDecl = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RT->getDecl());
1388
1389 // The destructor for an implicit anonymous union member is never invoked.
1390 if (FieldClassDecl->isUnion() && FieldClassDecl->isAnonymousStructOrUnion())
1391 return false;
1392
1393 return HasTrivialDestructorBody(Context, FieldClassDecl, FieldClassDecl);
1394}

1396/// CanSkipVTablePointerInitialization - Check whether we need to initialize
1397/// any vtable pointers before calling this destructor.
1398static bool CanSkipVTablePointerInitialization(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1399 const CXXDestructorDecl *Dtor) {
1400 const CXXRecordDecl *ClassDecl = Dtor->getParent();
1401 if (!ClassDecl->isDynamicClass())
1402 return true;
1403
1404 if (!Dtor->hasTrivialBody())
1405 return false;
1406
1407 // Check the fields.
1408 for (const auto *Field : ClassDecl->fields())
1409 if (!FieldHasTrivialDestructorBody(CGF.getContext(), Field))
1410 return false;
1411
1412 return true;
1413}

1415/// EmitDestructorBody - Emits the body of the current destructor.
1416void CodeGenFunction::EmitDestructorBody(FunctionArgList &Args) {
1417 const CXXDestructorDecl *Dtor = cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(CurGD.getDecl());
1418 CXXDtorType DtorType = CurGD.getDtorType();
1419
1420 // For an abstract class, non-base destructors are never used (and can't
1421 // be emitted in general, because vbase dtors may not have been validated
1422 // by Sema), but the Itanium ABI doesn't make them optional and Clang may
1423 // in fact emit references to them from other compilations, so emit them
1424 // as functions containing a trap instruction.
1425 if (DtorType != Dtor_Base && Dtor->getParent()->isAbstract()) {
1426 llvm::CallInst *TrapCall = EmitTrapCall(llvm::Intrinsic::trap);
1427 TrapCall->setDoesNotReturn();
1428 TrapCall->setDoesNotThrow();
1429 Builder.CreateUnreachable();
1430 Builder.ClearInsertionPoint();
1431 return;
1432 }
1433
1434 Stmt *Body = Dtor->getBody();
1435 if (Body)
1436 incrementProfileCounter(Body);
1437
1438 // The call to operator delete in a deleting destructor happens
1439 // outside of the function-try-block, which means it's always
1440 // possible to delegate the destructor body to the complete
1441 // destructor. Do so.
1442 if (DtorType == Dtor_Deleting) {
1443 RunCleanupsScope DtorEpilogue(*this);
1444 EnterDtorCleanups(Dtor, Dtor_Deleting);
1445 if (HaveInsertPoint())
1446 EmitCXXDestructorCall(Dtor, Dtor_Complete, /*ForVirtualBase=*/false,
1447 /*Delegating=*/false, LoadCXXThisAddress());
1448 return;
1449 }
1450
1451 // If the body is a function-try-block, enter the try before
1452 // anything else.
1453 bool isTryBody = (Body && isa<CXXTryStmt>(Body));
1454 if (isTryBody)
1455 EnterCXXTryStmt(*cast<CXXTryStmt>(Body), true);
1456 EmitAsanPrologueOrEpilogue(false);
1457
1458 // Enter the epilogue cleanups.
1459 RunCleanupsScope DtorEpilogue(*this);
1460
1461 // If this is the complete variant, just invoke the base variant;
1462 // the epilogue will destruct the virtual bases. But we can't do
1463 // this optimization if the body is a function-try-block, because
1464 // we'd introduce *two* handler blocks. In the Microsoft ABI, we
1465 // always delegate because we might not have a definition in this TU.
1466 switch (DtorType) {
1467 case Dtor_Comdat: llvm_unreachable("not expecting a COMDAT");
1468 case Dtor_Deleting: llvm_unreachable("already handled deleting case");
1469
1470 case Dtor_Complete:
1471 assert((Body || getTarget().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft()) &&
1472 "can't emit a dtor without a body for non-Microsoft ABIs");
1473
1474 // Enter the cleanup scopes for virtual bases.
1475 EnterDtorCleanups(Dtor, Dtor_Complete);
1476
1477 if (!isTryBody) {
1478 EmitCXXDestructorCall(Dtor, Dtor_Base, /*ForVirtualBase=*/false,
1479 /*Delegating=*/false, LoadCXXThisAddress());
1480 break;
1481 }
1482
1483 // Fallthrough: act like we're in the base variant.
1484 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
1485
1486 case Dtor_Base:
1487 assert(Body);
1488
1489 // Enter the cleanup scopes for fields and non-virtual bases.
1490 EnterDtorCleanups(Dtor, Dtor_Base);
1491
1492 // Initialize the vtable pointers before entering the body.
1493 if (!CanSkipVTablePointerInitialization(*this, Dtor)) {
1494 // Insert the llvm.launder.invariant.group intrinsic before initializing
1495 // the vptrs to cancel any previous assumptions we might have made.
1496 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().StrictVTablePointers &&
1497 CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel > 0)
1498 CXXThisValue = Builder.CreateLaunderInvariantGroup(LoadCXXThis());
1499 InitializeVTablePointers(Dtor->getParent());
1500 }
1501
1502 if (isTryBody)
1503 EmitStmt(cast<CXXTryStmt>(Body)->getTryBlock());
1504 else if (Body)
1505 EmitStmt(Body);
1506 else {
1507 assert(Dtor->isImplicit() && "bodyless dtor not implicit");
1508 // nothing to do besides what's in the epilogue
1509 }
1510 // -fapple-kext must inline any call to this dtor into
1511 // the caller's body.
1512 if (getLangOpts().AppleKext)
1513 CurFn->addFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::AlwaysInline);
1514
1515 break;
1516 }
1517
1518 // Jump out through the epilogue cleanups.
1519 DtorEpilogue.ForceCleanup();
1520
1521 // Exit the try if applicable.
1522 if (isTryBody)
1523 ExitCXXTryStmt(*cast<CXXTryStmt>(Body), true);
1524}

1526void CodeGenFunction::emitImplicitAssignmentOperatorBody(FunctionArgList &Args) {
1527 const CXXMethodDecl *AssignOp = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(CurGD.getDecl());
1528 const Stmt *RootS = AssignOp->getBody();
1529 assert(isa<CompoundStmt>(RootS) &&
1530 "Body of an implicit assignment operator should be compound stmt.");
1531 const CompoundStmt *RootCS = cast<CompoundStmt>(RootS);
1532
1533 LexicalScope Scope(*this, RootCS->getSourceRange());
1534
1535 incrementProfileCounter(RootCS);
1536 AssignmentMemcpyizer AM(*this, AssignOp, Args);
1537 for (auto *I : RootCS->body())
1538 AM.emitAssignment(I);
1539 AM.finish();
1540}

1550 /// Call the operator delete associated with the current destructor.
1551 struct CallDtorDelete final : EHScopeStack::Cleanup {
1552 CallDtorDelete() {}
1553
1554 void Emit(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Flags flags) override {
1555 const CXXDestructorDecl *Dtor = cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(CGF.CurCodeDecl);
1556 const CXXRecordDecl *ClassDecl = Dtor->getParent();
1557 CGF.EmitDeleteCall(Dtor->getOperatorDelete(),
1558 LoadThisForDtorDelete(CGF, Dtor),
1559 CGF.getContext().getTagDeclType(ClassDecl));
1560 }
1561 };

1563 void EmitConditionalDtorDeleteCall(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
1564 llvm::Value *ShouldDeleteCondition,
1565 bool ReturnAfterDelete) {
1566 llvm::BasicBlock *callDeleteBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("dtor.call_delete");
1567 llvm::BasicBlock *continueBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("dtor.continue");
1568 llvm::Value *ShouldCallDelete
1569 = CGF.Builder.CreateIsNull(ShouldDeleteCondition);
1570 CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(ShouldCallDelete, continueBB, callDeleteBB);
1571
1572 CGF.EmitBlock(callDeleteBB);
1573 const CXXDestructorDecl *Dtor = cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(CGF.CurCodeDecl);
1574 const CXXRecordDecl *ClassDecl = Dtor->getParent();
1575 CGF.EmitDeleteCall(Dtor->getOperatorDelete(),
1576 LoadThisForDtorDelete(CGF, Dtor),
1577 CGF.getContext().getTagDeclType(ClassDecl));
1578 assert(Dtor->getOperatorDelete()->isDestroyingOperatorDelete() ==
1579 ReturnAfterDelete &&
1580 "unexpected value for ReturnAfterDelete");
1581 if (ReturnAfterDelete)
1582 CGF.EmitBranchThroughCleanup(CGF.ReturnBlock);
1583 else
1584 CGF.Builder.CreateBr(continueBB);
1585
1586 CGF.EmitBlock(continueBB);
1587 }

1604 class DestroyField final : public EHScopeStack::Cleanup {
1605 const FieldDecl *field;
1606 CodeGenFunction::Destroyer *destroyer;
1607 bool useEHCleanupForArray;
1608
1609 public:
1610 DestroyField(const FieldDecl *field, CodeGenFunction::Destroyer *destroyer,
1611 bool useEHCleanupForArray)
1612 : field(field), destroyer(destroyer),
1613 useEHCleanupForArray(useEHCleanupForArray) {}
1614
1615 void Emit(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Flags flags) override {
1616 // Find the address of the field.
1617 Address thisValue = CGF.LoadCXXThisAddress();
1618 QualType RecordTy = CGF.getContext().getTagDeclType(field->getParent());
1619 LValue ThisLV = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(thisValue, RecordTy);
1620 LValue LV = CGF.EmitLValueForField(ThisLV, field);
1621 assert(LV.isSimple());
1622
1623 CGF.emitDestroy(LV.getAddress(), field->getType(), destroyer,
1624 flags.isForNormalCleanup() && useEHCleanupForArray);
1625 }

1628 static void EmitSanitizerDtorCallback(CodeGenFunction &CGF, llvm::Value *Ptr,
1629 CharUnits::QuantityType PoisonSize) {
1630 CodeGenFunction::SanitizerScope SanScope(&CGF);
1631 // Pass in void pointer and size of region as arguments to runtime
1632 // function
1633 llvm::Value *Args[] = {CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Ptr, CGF.VoidPtrTy),
1634 llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.SizeTy, PoisonSize)};
1635
1636 llvm::Type *ArgTypes[] = {CGF.VoidPtrTy, CGF.SizeTy};
1637
1638 llvm::FunctionType *FnType =
1639 llvm::FunctionType::get(CGF.VoidTy, ArgTypes, false);
1640 llvm::FunctionCallee Fn =
1641 CGF.CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(FnType, "__sanitizer_dtor_callback");
1642 CGF.EmitNounwindRuntimeCall(Fn, Args);
1643 }

1645 class SanitizeDtorMembers final : public EHScopeStack::Cleanup {
1646 const CXXDestructorDecl *Dtor;
1647
1648 public:
1649 SanitizeDtorMembers(const CXXDestructorDecl *Dtor) : Dtor(Dtor) {}
1650
1651 // Generate function call for handling object poisoning.
1652 // Disables tail call elimination, to prevent the current stack frame
1653 // from disappearing from the stack trace.
1654 void Emit(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Flags flags) override {
1655 const ASTRecordLayout &Layout =
1656 CGF.getContext().getASTRecordLayout(Dtor->getParent());
1657
1658 // Nothing to poison.
1659 if (Layout.getFieldCount() == 0)
1660 return;
1661
1662 // Prevent the current stack frame from disappearing from the stack trace.
1663 CGF.CurFn->addFnAttr("disable-tail-calls", "true");
1664
1665 // Construct pointer to region to begin poisoning, and calculate poison
1666 // size, so that only members declared in this class are poisoned.
1667 ASTContext &Context = CGF.getContext();
1668 unsigned fieldIndex = 0;
1669 int startIndex = -1;
1670 // RecordDecl::field_iterator Field;
1671 for (const FieldDecl *Field : Dtor->getParent()->fields()) {
1672 // Poison field if it is trivial
1673 if (FieldHasTrivialDestructorBody(Context, Field)) {
1674 // Start sanitizing at this field
1675 if (startIndex < 0)
1676 startIndex = fieldIndex;
1677
1678 // Currently on the last field, and it must be poisoned with the
1679 // current block.
1680 if (fieldIndex == Layout.getFieldCount() - 1) {
1681 PoisonMembers(CGF, startIndex, Layout.getFieldCount());
1682 }
1683 } else if (startIndex >= 0) {
1684 // No longer within a block of memory to poison, so poison the block
1685 PoisonMembers(CGF, startIndex, fieldIndex);
1686 // Re-set the start index
1687 startIndex = -1;
1688 }
1689 fieldIndex += 1;
1690 }
1691 }
1692
1693 private:
1694 /// \param layoutStartOffset index of the ASTRecordLayout field to
1695 /// start poisoning (inclusive)
1696 /// \param layoutEndOffset index of the ASTRecordLayout field to
1697 /// end poisoning (exclusive)
1698 void PoisonMembers(CodeGenFunction &CGF, unsigned layoutStartOffset,
1699 unsigned layoutEndOffset) {
1700 ASTContext &Context = CGF.getContext();
1701 const ASTRecordLayout &Layout =
1702 Context.getASTRecordLayout(Dtor->getParent());
1703
1704 llvm::ConstantInt *OffsetSizePtr = llvm::ConstantInt::get(
1705 CGF.SizeTy,
1706 Context.toCharUnitsFromBits(Layout.getFieldOffset(layoutStartOffset))
1707 .getQuantity());
1708
1709 llvm::Value *OffsetPtr = CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(
1710 CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(CGF.LoadCXXThis(), CGF.Int8PtrTy),
1711 OffsetSizePtr);
1712
1713 CharUnits::QuantityType PoisonSize;
1714 if (layoutEndOffset >= Layout.getFieldCount()) {
1715 PoisonSize = Layout.getNonVirtualSize().getQuantity() -
1716 Context.toCharUnitsFromBits(
1717 Layout.getFieldOffset(layoutStartOffset))
1718 .getQuantity();
1719 } else {
1720 PoisonSize = Context.toCharUnitsFromBits(
1721 Layout.getFieldOffset(layoutEndOffset) -
1722 Layout.getFieldOffset(layoutStartOffset))
1723 .getQuantity();
1724 }
1725
1726 if (PoisonSize == 0)
1727 return;
1728
1729 EmitSanitizerDtorCallback(CGF, OffsetPtr, PoisonSize);
1730 }
1731 };

1733 class SanitizeDtorVTable final : public EHScopeStack::Cleanup {
1734 const CXXDestructorDecl *Dtor;
1735
1736 public:
1737 SanitizeDtorVTable(const CXXDestructorDecl *Dtor) : Dtor(Dtor) {}
1738
1739 // Generate function call for handling vtable pointer poisoning.
1740 void Emit(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Flags flags) override {
1741 assert(Dtor->getParent()->isDynamicClass());
1742 (void)Dtor;
1743 ASTContext &Context = CGF.getContext();
1744 // Poison vtable and vtable ptr if they exist for this class.
1745 llvm::Value *VTablePtr = CGF.LoadCXXThis();
1746
1747 CharUnits::QuantityType PoisonSize =
1748 Context.toCharUnitsFromBits(CGF.PointerWidthInBits).getQuantity();
1749 // Pass in void pointer and size of region as arguments to runtime
1750 // function
1751 EmitSanitizerDtorCallback(CGF, VTablePtr, PoisonSize);
1752 }
1753 };

1756/// Emit all code that comes at the end of class's
1757/// destructor. This is to call destructors on members and base classes
1758/// in reverse order of their construction.
1759///
1760/// For a deleting destructor, this also handles the case where a destroying
1761/// operator delete completely overrides the definition.
1762void CodeGenFunction::EnterDtorCleanups(const CXXDestructorDecl *DD,
1763 CXXDtorType DtorType) {
1764 assert((!DD->isTrivial() || DD->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>()) &&
1765 "Should not emit dtor epilogue for non-exported trivial dtor!");
1766
1767 // The deleting-destructor phase just needs to call the appropriate
1768 // operator delete that Sema picked up.
1769 if (DtorType == Dtor_Deleting) {
1770 assert(DD->getOperatorDelete() &&
1771 "operator delete missing - EnterDtorCleanups");
1772 if (CXXStructorImplicitParamValue) {
1773 // If there is an implicit param to the deleting dtor, it's a boolean
1774 // telling whether this is a deleting destructor.
1775 if (DD->getOperatorDelete()->isDestroyingOperatorDelete())
1776 EmitConditionalDtorDeleteCall(*this, CXXStructorImplicitParamValue,
1777 /*ReturnAfterDelete*/true);
1778 else
1779 EHStack.pushCleanup<CallDtorDeleteConditional>(
1780 NormalAndEHCleanup, CXXStructorImplicitParamValue);
1781 } else {
1782 if (DD->getOperatorDelete()->isDestroyingOperatorDelete()) {
1783 const CXXRecordDecl *ClassDecl = DD->getParent();
1784 EmitDeleteCall(DD->getOperatorDelete(),
1785 LoadThisForDtorDelete(*this, DD),
1786 getContext().getTagDeclType(ClassDecl));
1787 EmitBranchThroughCleanup(ReturnBlock);
1788 } else {
1789 EHStack.pushCleanup<CallDtorDelete>(NormalAndEHCleanup);
1790 }
1791 }
1792 return;
1793 }
1794
1795 const CXXRecordDecl *ClassDecl = DD->getParent();
1796
1797 // Unions have no bases and do not call field destructors.
1798 if (ClassDecl->isUnion())
1799 return;
1800
1801 // The complete-destructor phase just destructs all the virtual bases.
1802 if (DtorType == Dtor_Complete) {
1803 // Poison the vtable pointer such that access after the base
1804 // and member destructors are invoked is invalid.
1805 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeMemoryUseAfterDtor &&
1806 SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Memory) && ClassDecl->getNumVBases() &&
1807 ClassDecl->isPolymorphic())
1808 EHStack.pushCleanup<SanitizeDtorVTable>(NormalAndEHCleanup, DD);
1809
1810 // We push them in the forward order so that they'll be popped in
1811 // the reverse order.
1812 for (const auto &Base : ClassDecl->vbases()) {
1813 CXXRecordDecl *BaseClassDecl
1814 = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Base.getType()->getAs<RecordType>()->getDecl());
1815
1816 // Ignore trivial destructors.
1817 if (BaseClassDecl->hasTrivialDestructor())
1818 continue;
1819
1820 EHStack.pushCleanup<CallBaseDtor>(NormalAndEHCleanup,
1821 BaseClassDecl,
1822 /*BaseIsVirtual*/ true);
1823 }
1824
1825 return;
1826 }
1827
1828 assert(DtorType == Dtor_Base);
1829 // Poison the vtable pointer if it has no virtual bases, but inherits
1830 // virtual functions.
1831 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeMemoryUseAfterDtor &&
1832 SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Memory) && !ClassDecl->getNumVBases() &&
1833 ClassDecl->isPolymorphic())
1834 EHStack.pushCleanup<SanitizeDtorVTable>(NormalAndEHCleanup, DD);
1835
1836 // Destroy non-virtual bases.
1837 for (const auto &Base : ClassDecl->bases()) {
1838 // Ignore virtual bases.
1839 if (Base.isVirtual())
1840 continue;
1841
1842 CXXRecordDecl *BaseClassDecl = Base.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
1843
1844 // Ignore trivial destructors.
1845 if (BaseClassDecl->hasTrivialDestructor())
1846 continue;
1847
1848 EHStack.pushCleanup<CallBaseDtor>(NormalAndEHCleanup,
1849 BaseClassDecl,
1850 /*BaseIsVirtual*/ false);
1851 }
1852
1853 // Poison fields such that access after their destructors are
1854 // invoked, and before the base class destructor runs, is invalid.
1855 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeMemoryUseAfterDtor &&
1856 SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::Memory))
1857 EHStack.pushCleanup<SanitizeDtorMembers>(NormalAndEHCleanup, DD);
1858
1859 // Destroy direct fields.
1860 for (const auto *Field : ClassDecl->fields()) {
1861 QualType type = Field->getType();
1862 QualType::DestructionKind dtorKind = type.isDestructedType();
1863 if (!dtorKind) continue;
1864
1865 // Anonymous union members do not have their destructors called.
1866 const RecordType *RT = type->getAsUnionType();
1867 if (RT && RT->getDecl()->isAnonymousStructOrUnion()) continue;
1868
1869 CleanupKind cleanupKind = getCleanupKind(dtorKind);
1870 EHStack.pushCleanup<DestroyField>(cleanupKind, Field,
1871 getDestroyer(dtorKind),
1872 cleanupKind & EHCleanup);
1873 }
1874}
