1896/// EmitCXXAggrConstructorCall - Emit a loop to call a particular
1897/// constructor for each of several members of an array.
1898///
1899/// \param ctor the constructor to call for each element
1900/// \param numElements the number of elements in the array;
1901/// may be zero
1902/// \param arrayBase a T*, where T is the type constructed by ctor
1903/// \param zeroInitialize true if each element should be
1904/// zero-initialized before it is constructed
1905void CodeGenFunction::EmitCXXAggrConstructorCall(const CXXConstructorDecl *ctor,
1906 llvm::Value *numElements,
1907 Address arrayBase,
1908 const CXXConstructExpr *E,
1909 bool NewPointerIsChecked,
1910 bool zeroInitialize) {
1911 // It's legal for numElements to be zero. This can happen both
1912 // dynamically, because x can be zero in 'new A[x]', and statically,
1913 // because of GCC extensions that permit zero-length arrays. There
1914 // are probably legitimate places where we could assume that this
1915 // doesn't happen, but it's not clear that it's worth it.
1916 llvm::BranchInst *zeroCheckBranch = nullptr;
1917
1918 // Optimize for a constant count.
1919 llvm::ConstantInt *constantCount
1920 = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(numElements);
1921 if (constantCount) {
1922 // Just skip out if the constant count is zero.
1923 if (constantCount->isZero()) return;
1924
1925 // Otherwise, emit the check.
1926 } else {
1927 llvm::BasicBlock *loopBB = createBasicBlock("new.ctorloop");
1928 llvm::Value *iszero = Builder.CreateIsNull(numElements, "isempty");
1929 zeroCheckBranch = Builder.CreateCondBr(iszero, loopBB, loopBB);
1930 EmitBlock(loopBB);
1931 }
1932
1933 // Find the end of the array.
1934 llvm::Value *arrayBegin = arrayBase.getPointer();
1935 llvm::Value *arrayEnd = Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(arrayBegin, numElements,
1936 "arrayctor.end");
1937
1938 // Enter the loop, setting up a phi for the current location to initialize.
1939 llvm::BasicBlock *entryBB = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
1940 llvm::BasicBlock *loopBB = createBasicBlock("arrayctor.loop");
1941 EmitBlock(loopBB);
1942 llvm::PHINode *cur = Builder.CreatePHI(arrayBegin->getType(), 2,
1943 "arrayctor.cur");
1944 cur->addIncoming(arrayBegin, entryBB);
1945
1946 // Inside the loop body, emit the constructor call on the array element.
1947
1948 // The alignment of the base, adjusted by the size of a single element,
1949 // provides a conservative estimate of the alignment of every element.
1950 // (This assumes we never start tracking offsetted alignments.)
1951 //
1952 // Note that these are complete objects and so we don't need to
1953 // use the non-virtual size or alignment.
1954 QualType type = getContext().getTypeDeclType(ctor->getParent());
1955 CharUnits eltAlignment =
1956 arrayBase.getAlignment()
1957 .alignmentOfArrayElement(getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(type));
1958 Address curAddr = Address(cur, eltAlignment);
1959
1960 // Zero initialize the storage, if requested.
1961 if (zeroInitialize)
1962 EmitNullInitialization(curAddr, type);
1963
1964 // C++ [class.temporary]p4:
1965 // There are two contexts in which temporaries are destroyed at a different
1966 // point than the end of the full-expression. The first context is when a
1967 // default constructor is called to initialize an element of an array.
1968 // If the constructor has one or more default arguments, the destruction of
1969 // every temporary created in a default argument expression is sequenced
1970 // before the construction of the next array element, if any.
1971
1972 {
1973 RunCleanupsScope Scope(*this);
1974
1975 // Evaluate the constructor and its arguments in a regular
1976 // partial-destroy cleanup.
1977 if (getLangOpts().Exceptions &&
1978 !ctor->getParent()->hasTrivialDestructor()) {
1979 Destroyer *destroyer = destroyCXXObject;
1980 pushRegularPartialArrayCleanup(arrayBegin, cur, type, eltAlignment,
1981 *destroyer);
1982 }
1983 auto currAVS = AggValueSlot::forAddr(
1984 curAddr, type.getQualifiers(), AggValueSlot::IsDestructed,
1985 AggValueSlot::DoesNotNeedGCBarriers, AggValueSlot::IsNotAliased,
1986 AggValueSlot::DoesNotOverlap, AggValueSlot::IsNotZeroed,
1987 NewPointerIsChecked ? AggValueSlot::IsSanitizerChecked
1988 : AggValueSlot::IsNotSanitizerChecked);
1989 EmitCXXConstructorCall(ctor, Ctor_Complete, /*ForVirtualBase=*/false,
1990 /*Delegating=*/false, currAVS, E);
1991 }
1992
1993 // Go to the next element.
1994 llvm::Value *next =
1995 Builder.CreateInBoundsGEP(cur, llvm::ConstantInt::get(SizeTy, 1),
1996 "arrayctor.next");
1997 cur->addIncoming(next, Builder.GetInsertBlock());
1998
1999 // Check whether that's the end of the loop.
2000 llvm::Value *done = Builder.CreateICmpEQ(next, arrayEnd, "arrayctor.done");
2001 llvm::BasicBlock *contBB = createBasicBlock("arrayctor.cont");
2002 Builder.CreateCondBr(done, contBB, loopBB);
2003
2004 // Patch the earlier check to skip over the loop.
2005 if (zeroCheckBranch) zeroCheckBranch->setSuccessor(0, contBB);
2006
2007 EmitBlock(contBB);
2008}
2009
2010void CodeGenFunction::destroyCXXObject(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2011 Address addr,
2012 QualType type) {
2013 const RecordType *rtype = type->castAs<RecordType>();
2014 const CXXRecordDecl *record = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(rtype->getDecl());
2015 const CXXDestructorDecl *dtor = record->getDestructor();
2016 assert(!dtor->isTrivial());
2017 CGF.EmitCXXDestructorCall(dtor, Dtor_Complete, /*for vbase*/ false,
2018 /*Delegating=*/false, addr);
2019}
2020
2021void CodeGenFunction::EmitCXXConstructorCall(const CXXConstructorDecl *D,
2022 CXXCtorType Type,
2023 bool ForVirtualBase,
2024 bool Delegating,
2025 AggValueSlot ThisAVS,
2026 const CXXConstructExpr *E) {
2027 CallArgList Args;
2028 Address This = ThisAVS.getAddress();
2029 LangAS SlotAS = ThisAVS.getQualifiers().getAddressSpace();
2030 QualType ThisType = D->getThisType();
2031 LangAS ThisAS = ThisType.getTypePtr()->getPointeeType().getAddressSpace();
2032 llvm::Value *ThisPtr = This.getPointer();
2033
2034 if (SlotAS != ThisAS) {
2035 unsigned TargetThisAS = getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(ThisAS);
2036 llvm::Type *NewType =
2037 ThisPtr->getType()->getPointerElementType()->getPointerTo(TargetThisAS);
2038 ThisPtr = getTargetHooks().performAddrSpaceCast(*this, This.getPointer(),
2039 ThisAS, SlotAS, NewType);
2040 }
2041
2042 // Push the this ptr.
2043 Args.add(RValue::get(ThisPtr), D->getThisType());
2044
2045 // If this is a trivial constructor, emit a memcpy now before we lose
2046 // the alignment information on the argument.
2047 // FIXME: It would be better to preserve alignment information into CallArg.
2048 if (isMemcpyEquivalentSpecialMember(D)) {
2049 assert(E->getNumArgs() == 1 && "unexpected argcount for trivial ctor");
2050
2051 const Expr *Arg = E->getArg(0);
2052 LValue Src = EmitLValue(Arg);
2053 QualType DestTy = getContext().getTypeDeclType(D->getParent());
2054 LValue Dest = MakeAddrLValue(This, DestTy);
2055 EmitAggregateCopyCtor(Dest, Src, ThisAVS.mayOverlap());
2056 return;
2057 }
2058
2059 // Add the rest of the user-supplied arguments.
2060 const FunctionProtoType *FPT = D->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
2061 EvaluationOrder Order = E->isListInitialization()
2062 ? EvaluationOrder::ForceLeftToRight
2063 : EvaluationOrder::Default;
2064 EmitCallArgs(Args, FPT, E->arguments(), E->getConstructor(),
2065 /*ParamsToSkip*/ 0, Order);
2066
2067 EmitCXXConstructorCall(D, Type, ForVirtualBase, Delegating, This, Args,
2068 ThisAVS.mayOverlap(), E->getExprLoc(),
2069 ThisAVS.isSanitizerChecked());
2070}
2071
2072static bool canEmitDelegateCallArgs(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
2073 const CXXConstructorDecl *Ctor,
2074 CXXCtorType Type, CallArgList &Args) {
2075 // We can't forward a variadic call.
2076 if (Ctor->isVariadic())
2077 return false;
2078
2079 if (CGF.getTarget().getCXXABI().areArgsDestroyedLeftToRightInCallee()) {
2080 // If the parameters are callee-cleanup, it's not safe to forward.
2081 for (auto *P : Ctor->parameters())
2082 if (P->getType().isDestructedType())
2083 return false;
2084
2085 // Likewise if they're inalloca.
2086 const CGFunctionInfo &Info =
2087 CGF.CGM.getTypes().arrangeCXXConstructorCall(Args, Ctor, Type, 0, 0);
2088 if (Info.usesInAlloca())
2089 return false;
2090 }
2091
2092 // Anything else should be OK.
2093 return true;
2094}
2095
2096void CodeGenFunction::EmitCXXConstructorCall(const CXXConstructorDecl *D,
2097 CXXCtorType Type,
2098 bool ForVirtualBase,
2099 bool Delegating,
2100 Address This,
2101 CallArgList &Args,
2102 AggValueSlot::Overlap_t Overlap,
2103 SourceLocation Loc,
2104 bool NewPointerIsChecked) {
2105 const CXXRecordDecl *ClassDecl = D->getParent();
2106
2107 if (!NewPointerIsChecked)
2108 EmitTypeCheck(CodeGenFunction::TCK_ConstructorCall, Loc, This.getPointer(),
2109 getContext().getRecordType(ClassDecl), CharUnits::Zero());
2110
2111 if (D->isTrivial() && D->isDefaultConstructor()) {
2112 assert(Args.size() == 1 && "trivial default ctor with args");
2113 return;
2114 }
2115
2116 // If this is a trivial constructor, just emit what's needed. If this is a
2117 // union copy constructor, we must emit a memcpy, because the AST does not
2118 // model that copy.
2119 if (isMemcpyEquivalentSpecialMember(D)) {
2120 assert(Args.size() == 2 && "unexpected argcount for trivial ctor");
2121
2122 QualType SrcTy = D->getParamDecl(0)->getType().getNonReferenceType();
2123 Address Src(Args[1].getRValue(*this).getScalarVal(),
2124 getNaturalTypeAlignment(SrcTy));
2125 LValue SrcLVal = MakeAddrLValue(Src, SrcTy);
2126 QualType DestTy = getContext().getTypeDeclType(ClassDecl);
2127 LValue DestLVal = MakeAddrLValue(This, DestTy);
2128 EmitAggregateCopyCtor(DestLVal, SrcLVal, Overlap);
2129 return;
2130 }
2131
2132 bool PassPrototypeArgs = true;
2133 // Check whether we can actually emit the constructor before trying to do so.
2134 if (auto Inherited = D->getInheritedConstructor()) {
2135 PassPrototypeArgs = getTypes().inheritingCtorHasParams(Inherited, Type);
2136 if (PassPrototypeArgs && !canEmitDelegateCallArgs(*this, D, Type, Args)) {
2137 EmitInlinedInheritingCXXConstructorCall(D, Type, ForVirtualBase,
2138 Delegating, Args);
2139 return;
2140 }
2141 }
2142
2143 // Insert any ABI-specific implicit constructor arguments.
2144 CGCXXABI::AddedStructorArgs ExtraArgs =
2145 CGM.getCXXABI().addImplicitConstructorArgs(*this, D, Type, ForVirtualBase,
2146 Delegating, Args);
2147
2148 // Emit the call.
2149 llvm::Constant *CalleePtr = CGM.getAddrOfCXXStructor(GlobalDecl(D, Type));
2150 const CGFunctionInfo &Info = CGM.getTypes().arrangeCXXConstructorCall(
2151 Args, D, Type, ExtraArgs.Prefix, ExtraArgs.Suffix, PassPrototypeArgs);
2152 CGCallee Callee = CGCallee::forDirect(CalleePtr, GlobalDecl(D, Type));
2153 EmitCall(Info, Callee, ReturnValueSlot(), Args);
2154
2155 // Generate vtable assumptions if we're constructing a complete object
2156 // with a vtable. We don't do this for base subobjects for two reasons:
2157 // first, it's incorrect for classes with virtual bases, and second, we're
2158 // about to overwrite the vptrs anyway.
2159 // We also have to make sure if we can refer to vtable:
2160 // - Otherwise we can refer to vtable if it's safe to speculatively emit.
2161 // FIXME: If vtable is used by ctor/dtor, or if vtable is external and we are
2162 // sure that definition of vtable is not hidden,
2163 // then we are always safe to refer to it.
2164 // FIXME: It looks like InstCombine is very inefficient on dealing with
2165 // assumes. Make assumption loads require -fstrict-vtable-pointers temporarily.
2166 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel > 0 &&
2167 ClassDecl->isDynamicClass() && Type != Ctor_Base &&
2168 CGM.getCXXABI().canSpeculativelyEmitVTable(ClassDecl) &&
2169 CGM.getCodeGenOpts().StrictVTablePointers)
2170 EmitVTableAssumptionLoads(ClassDecl, This);
2171}
2172
2173void CodeGenFunction::EmitInheritedCXXConstructorCall(
2174 const CXXConstructorDecl *D, bool ForVirtualBase, Address This,
2175 bool InheritedFromVBase, const CXXInheritedCtorInitExpr *E) {
2176 CallArgList Args;
2177 CallArg ThisArg(
2178 RValue::get(This.getPointer(), This.getAlignment().getQuantity()),
2179 D->getThisType());
2180
2181 // Forward the parameters.
2182 if (InheritedFromVBase &&
2183 CGM.getTarget().getCXXABI().hasConstructorVariants()) {
2184 // Nothing to do; this construction is not responsible for constructing
2185 // the base class containing the inherited constructor.
2186 // FIXME: Can we just pass undef's for the remaining arguments if we don't
2187 // have constructor variants?
2188 Args.push_back(ThisArg);
2189 } else if (!CXXInheritedCtorInitExprArgs.empty()) {
2190 // The inheriting constructor was inlined; just inject its arguments.
2191 assert(CXXInheritedCtorInitExprArgs.size() >= D->getNumParams() &&
2192 "wrong number of parameters for inherited constructor call");
2193 Args = CXXInheritedCtorInitExprArgs;
2194 Args[0] = ThisArg;
2195 } else {
2196 // The inheriting constructor was not inlined. Emit delegating arguments.
2197 Args.push_back(ThisArg);
2198 const auto *OuterCtor = cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(CurCodeDecl);
2199 assert(OuterCtor->getNumParams() == D->getNumParams());
2200 assert(!OuterCtor->isVariadic() && "should have been inlined");
2201
2202 for (const auto *Param : OuterCtor->parameters()) {
2203 assert(getContext().hasSameUnqualifiedType(
2204 OuterCtor->getParamDecl(Param->getFunctionScopeIndex())->getType(),
2205 Param->getType()));
2206 EmitDelegateCallArg(Args, Param, E->getLocation());
2207
2208 // Forward __attribute__(pass_object_size).
2209 if (Param->hasAttr<PassObjectSizeAttr>()) {
2210 auto *POSParam = SizeArguments[Param];
2211 assert(POSParam && "missing pass_object_size value for forwarding");
2212 EmitDelegateCallArg(Args, POSParam, E->getLocation());
2213 }
2214 }
2215 }
2216
2217 EmitCXXConstructorCall(D, Ctor_Base, ForVirtualBase, /*Delegating*/false,
2218 This, Args, AggValueSlot::MayOverlap,
2219 E->getLocation(), /*NewPointerIsChecked*/true);
2220}
2221
2222void CodeGenFunction::EmitInlinedInheritingCXXConstructorCall(
2223 const CXXConstructorDecl *Ctor, CXXCtorType CtorType, bool ForVirtualBase,
2224 bool Delegating, CallArgList &Args) {
2225 GlobalDecl GD(Ctor, CtorType);
2226 InlinedInheritingConstructorScope Scope(*this, GD);
2227 ApplyInlineDebugLocation DebugScope(*this, GD);
2228 RunCleanupsScope RunCleanups(*this);
2229
2230 // Save the arguments to be passed to the inherited constructor.
2231 CXXInheritedCtorInitExprArgs = Args;
2232
2233 FunctionArgList Params;
2234 QualType RetType = BuildFunctionArgList(CurGD, Params);
2235 FnRetTy = RetType;
2236
2237 // Insert any ABI-specific implicit constructor arguments.
2238 CGM.getCXXABI().addImplicitConstructorArgs(*this, Ctor, CtorType,
2239 ForVirtualBase, Delegating, Args);
2240
2241 // Emit a simplified prolog. We only need to emit the implicit params.
2242 assert(Args.size() >= Params.size() && "too few arguments for call");
2243 for (unsigned I = 0, N = Args.size(); I != N; ++I) {
2244 if (I < Params.size() && isa<ImplicitParamDecl>(Params[I])) {
2245 const RValue &RV = Args[I].getRValue(*this);
2246 assert(!RV.isComplex() && "complex indirect params not supported");
2247 ParamValue Val = RV.isScalar()
2248 ? ParamValue::forDirect(RV.getScalarVal())
2249 : ParamValue::forIndirect(RV.getAggregateAddress());
2250 EmitParmDecl(*Params[I], Val, I + 1);
2251 }
2252 }
2253
2254 // Create a return value slot if the ABI implementation wants one.
2255 // FIXME: This is dumb, we should ask the ABI not to try to set the return
2256 // value instead.
2257 if (!RetType->isVoidType())
2258 ReturnValue = CreateIRTemp(RetType, "retval.inhctor");
2259
2260 CGM.getCXXABI().EmitInstanceFunctionProlog(*this);
2261 CXXThisValue = CXXABIThisValue;
2262
2263 // Directly emit the constructor initializers.
2264 EmitCtorPrologue(Ctor, CtorType, Params);
2265}

2267void CodeGenFunction::EmitVTableAssumptionLoad(const VPtr &Vptr, Address This) {
2268 llvm::Value *VTableGlobal =
2269 CGM.getCXXABI().getVTableAddressPoint(Vptr.Base, Vptr.VTableClass);
2270 if (!VTableGlobal)
2271 return;
2272
2273 // We can just use the base offset in the complete class.
2274 CharUnits NonVirtualOffset = Vptr.Base.getBaseOffset();
2275
2276 if (!NonVirtualOffset.isZero())
2277 This =
2278 ApplyNonVirtualAndVirtualOffset(*this, This, NonVirtualOffset, nullptr,
2279 Vptr.VTableClass, Vptr.NearestVBase);
2280
2281 llvm::Value *VPtrValue =
2282 GetVTablePtr(This, VTableGlobal->getType(), Vptr.VTableClass);
2283 llvm::Value *Cmp =
2284 Builder.CreateICmpEQ(VPtrValue, VTableGlobal, "cmp.vtables");
2285 Builder.CreateAssumption(Cmp);
2286}

2288void CodeGenFunction::EmitVTableAssumptionLoads(const CXXRecordDecl *ClassDecl,
2289 Address This) {
2290 if (CGM.getCXXABI().doStructorsInitializeVPtrs(ClassDecl))
2291 for (const VPtr &Vptr : getVTablePointers(ClassDecl))
2292 EmitVTableAssumptionLoad(Vptr, This);
2293}

2295void
2296CodeGenFunction::EmitSynthesizedCXXCopyCtorCall(const CXXConstructorDecl *D,
2297 Address This, Address Src,
2298 const CXXConstructExpr *E) {
2299 const FunctionProtoType *FPT = D->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
2300
2301 CallArgList Args;
2302
2303 // Push the this ptr.
2304 Args.add(RValue::get(This.getPointer(), This.getAlignment().getQuantity()),
2305 D->getThisType());
2306
2307 // Push the src ptr.
2308 QualType QT = *(FPT->param_type_begin());
2309 llvm::Type *t = CGM.getTypes().ConvertType(QT);
2310 Src = Builder.CreateBitCast(Src, t);
2311 Args.add(RValue::get(Src.getPointer(), Src.getAlignment().getQuantity()), QT);
2312
2313 // Skip over first argument (Src).
2314 EmitCallArgs(Args, FPT, drop_begin(E->arguments(), 1), E->getConstructor(),
2315 /*ParamsToSkip*/ 1);
2316
2317 EmitCXXConstructorCall(D, Ctor_Complete, /*ForVirtualBase*/false,
2318 /*Delegating*/false, This, Args,
2319 AggValueSlot::MayOverlap, E->getExprLoc(),
2320 /*NewPointerIsChecked*/false);
2321}

2323void
2324CodeGenFunction::EmitDelegateCXXConstructorCall(const CXXConstructorDecl *Ctor,
2325 CXXCtorType CtorType,
2326 const FunctionArgList &Args,
2327 SourceLocation Loc) {
2328 CallArgList DelegateArgs;
2329
2330 FunctionArgList::const_iterator I = Args.begin(), E = Args.end();
2331 assert(I != E && "no parameters to constructor");
2332
2333 // this
2334 Address This = LoadCXXThisAddress();
2335 DelegateArgs.add(
2336 RValue::get(This.getPointer(), This.getAlignment().getQuantity()),
2337 (*I)->getType());
2338 ++I;
2339
2340 // FIXME: The location of the VTT parameter in the parameter list is
2341 // specific to the Itanium ABI and shouldn't be hardcoded here.
2342 if (CGM.getCXXABI().NeedsVTTParameter(CurGD)) {
2343 assert(I != E && "cannot skip vtt parameter, already done with args");
2344 assert((*I)->getType()->isPointerType() &&
2345 "skipping parameter not of vtt type");
2346 ++I;
2347 }
2348
2349 // Explicit arguments.
2350 for (; I != E; ++I) {
2351 const VarDecl *param = *I;
2352 // FIXME: per-argument source location
2353 EmitDelegateCallArg(DelegateArgs, param, Loc);
2354 }
2355
2356 EmitCXXConstructorCall(Ctor, CtorType, /*ForVirtualBase=*/false,
2357 /*Delegating=*/true, This, DelegateArgs,
2358 AggValueSlot::MayOverlap, Loc,
2359 /*NewPointerIsChecked=*/true);
2360}

2449void CodeGenFunction::InitializeVTablePointer(const VPtr &Vptr) {
2450 // Compute the address point.
2451 llvm::Value *VTableAddressPoint =
2452 CGM.getCXXABI().getVTableAddressPointInStructor(
2453 *this, Vptr.VTableClass, Vptr.Base, Vptr.NearestVBase);
2454
2455 if (!VTableAddressPoint)
2456 return;
2457
2458 // Compute where to store the address point.
2459 llvm::Value *VirtualOffset = nullptr;
2460 CharUnits NonVirtualOffset = CharUnits::Zero();
2461
2462 if (CGM.getCXXABI().isVirtualOffsetNeededForVTableField(*this, Vptr)) {
2463 // We need to use the virtual base offset offset because the virtual base
2464 // might have a different offset in the most derived class.
2465
2466 VirtualOffset = CGM.getCXXABI().GetVirtualBaseClassOffset(
2467 *this, LoadCXXThisAddress(), Vptr.VTableClass, Vptr.NearestVBase);
2468 NonVirtualOffset = Vptr.OffsetFromNearestVBase;
2469 } else {
2470 // We can just use the base offset in the complete class.
2471 NonVirtualOffset = Vptr.Base.getBaseOffset();
2472 }
2473
2474 // Apply the offsets.
2475 Address VTableField = LoadCXXThisAddress();
2476
2477 if (!NonVirtualOffset.isZero() || VirtualOffset)
2478 VTableField = ApplyNonVirtualAndVirtualOffset(
2479 *this, VTableField, NonVirtualOffset, VirtualOffset, Vptr.VTableClass,
2480 Vptr.NearestVBase);
2481
2482 // Finally, store the address point. Use the same LLVM types as the field to
2483 // support optimization.
2484 unsigned DefaultAS = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS();
2485 llvm::Type *VTablePtrTy =
2486 llvm::FunctionType::get(CGM.Int32Ty, /*isVarArg=*/true)
2487 ->getPointerTo(DefaultAS)
2488 ->getPointerTo(DefaultAS);
2489 VTableField = Builder.CreateBitCast(VTableField,
2490 VTablePtrTy->getPointerTo(DefaultAS));
2491 VTableAddressPoint = Builder.CreateBitCast(VTableAddressPoint, VTablePtrTy);
2492
2493 llvm::StoreInst *Store = Builder.CreateStore(VTableAddressPoint, VTableField);
2494 TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo = CGM.getTBAAVTablePtrAccessInfo(VTablePtrTy);
2495 CGM.DecorateInstructionWithTBAA(Store, TBAAInfo);
2496 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel > 0 &&
2497 CGM.getCodeGenOpts().StrictVTablePointers)
2498 CGM.DecorateInstructionWithInvariantGroup(Store, Vptr.VTableClass);
2499}

2501CodeGenFunction::VPtrsVector
2502CodeGenFunction::getVTablePointers(const CXXRecordDecl *VTableClass) {
2503 CodeGenFunction::VPtrsVector VPtrsResult;
2504 VisitedVirtualBasesSetTy VBases;
2505 getVTablePointers(BaseSubobject(VTableClass, CharUnits::Zero()),
2506 /*NearestVBase=*/nullptr,
2507 /*OffsetFromNearestVBase=*/CharUnits::Zero(),
2508 /*BaseIsNonVirtualPrimaryBase=*/false, VTableClass, VBases,
2509 VPtrsResult);
2510 return VPtrsResult;
2511}
2512
2513void CodeGenFunction::getVTablePointers(BaseSubobject Base,
2514 const CXXRecordDecl *NearestVBase,
2515 CharUnits OffsetFromNearestVBase,
2516 bool BaseIsNonVirtualPrimaryBase,
2517 const CXXRecordDecl *VTableClass,
2518 VisitedVirtualBasesSetTy &VBases,
2519 VPtrsVector &Vptrs) {
2520 // If this base is a non-virtual primary base the address point has already
2521 // been set.
2522 if (!BaseIsNonVirtualPrimaryBase) {
2523 // Initialize the vtable pointer for this base.
2524 VPtr Vptr = {Base, NearestVBase, OffsetFromNearestVBase, VTableClass};
2525 Vptrs.push_back(Vptr);
2526 }
2527
2528 const CXXRecordDecl *RD = Base.getBase();
2529
2530 // Traverse bases.
2531 for (const auto &I : RD->bases()) {
2532 CXXRecordDecl *BaseDecl
2533 = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(I.getType()->getAs<RecordType>()->getDecl());
2534
2535 // Ignore classes without a vtable.
2536 if (!BaseDecl->isDynamicClass())
2537 continue;
2538
2539 CharUnits BaseOffset;
2540 CharUnits BaseOffsetFromNearestVBase;
2541 bool BaseDeclIsNonVirtualPrimaryBase;
2542
2543 if (I.isVirtual()) {
2544 // Check if we've visited this virtual base before.
2545 if (!VBases.insert(BaseDecl).second)
2546 continue;
2547
2548 const ASTRecordLayout &Layout =
2549 getContext().getASTRecordLayout(VTableClass);
2550
2551 BaseOffset = Layout.getVBaseClassOffset(BaseDecl);
2552 BaseOffsetFromNearestVBase = CharUnits::Zero();
2553 BaseDeclIsNonVirtualPrimaryBase = false;
2554 } else {
2555 const ASTRecordLayout &Layout = getContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
2556
2557 BaseOffset = Base.getBaseOffset() + Layout.getBaseClassOffset(BaseDecl);
2558 BaseOffsetFromNearestVBase =
2559 OffsetFromNearestVBase + Layout.getBaseClassOffset(BaseDecl);
2560 BaseDeclIsNonVirtualPrimaryBase = Layout.getPrimaryBase() == BaseDecl;
2561 }
2562
2563 getVTablePointers(
2564 BaseSubobject(BaseDecl, BaseOffset),
2565 I.isVirtual() ? BaseDecl : NearestVBase, BaseOffsetFromNearestVBase,
2566 BaseDeclIsNonVirtualPrimaryBase, VTableClass, VBases, Vptrs);
2567 }
2568}
2569
2570void CodeGenFunction::InitializeVTablePointers(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
2571 // Ignore classes without a vtable.
2572 if (!RD->isDynamicClass())
2573 return;
2574
2575 // Initialize the vtable pointers for this class and all of its bases.
2576 if (CGM.getCXXABI().doStructorsInitializeVPtrs(RD))
2577 for (const VPtr &Vptr : getVTablePointers(RD))
2578 InitializeVTablePointer(Vptr);
2579
2580 if (RD->getNumVBases())
2581 CGM.getCXXABI().initializeHiddenVirtualInheritanceMembers(*this, RD);
2582}

2584llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::GetVTablePtr(Address This,
2585 llvm::Type *VTableTy,
2586 const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
2587 Address VTablePtrSrc = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(This, VTableTy);
2588 llvm::Instruction *VTable = Builder.CreateLoad(VTablePtrSrc, "vtable");
2589 TBAAAccessInfo TBAAInfo = CGM.getTBAAVTablePtrAccessInfo(VTableTy);
2590 CGM.DecorateInstructionWithTBAA(VTable, TBAAInfo);
2591
2592 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().OptimizationLevel > 0 &&
2593 CGM.getCodeGenOpts().StrictVTablePointers)
2594 CGM.DecorateInstructionWithInvariantGroup(VTable, RD);
2595
2596 return VTable;
2597}

2599// If a class has a single non-virtual base and does not introduce or override
2600// virtual member functions or fields, it will have the same layout as its base.
2601// This function returns the least derived such class.
2602//
2603// Casting an instance of a base class to such a derived class is technically
2604// undefined behavior, but it is a relatively common hack for introducing member
2605// functions on class instances with specific properties (e.g. llvm::Operator)
2606// that works under most compilers and should not have security implications, so
2607// we allow it by default. It can be disabled with -fsanitize=cfi-cast-strict.
2608static const CXXRecordDecl *
2609LeastDerivedClassWithSameLayout(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
2610 if (!RD->field_empty())
2611 return RD;
2612
2613 if (RD->getNumVBases() != 0)
2614 return RD;
2615
2616 if (RD->getNumBases() != 1)
2617 return RD;
2618
2619 for (const CXXMethodDecl *MD : RD->methods()) {
2620 if (MD->isVirtual()) {
2621 // Virtual member functions are only ok if they are implicit destructors
2622 // because the implicit destructor will have the same semantics as the
2623 // base class's destructor if no fields are added.
2624 if (isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(MD) && MD->isImplicit())
2625 continue;
2626 return RD;
2627 }
2628 }
2629
2630 return LeastDerivedClassWithSameLayout(
2631 RD->bases_begin()->getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl());
2632}

2634void CodeGenFunction::EmitTypeMetadataCodeForVCall(const CXXRecordDecl *RD,
2635 llvm::Value *VTable,
2636 SourceLocation Loc) {
2637 if (SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::CFIVCall))
2638 EmitVTablePtrCheckForCall(RD, VTable, CodeGenFunction::CFITCK_VCall, Loc);
2639 else if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().WholeProgramVTables &&
2640 CGM.HasHiddenLTOVisibility(RD)) {
2641 llvm::Metadata *MD =
2642 CGM.CreateMetadataIdentifierForType(QualType(RD->getTypeForDecl(), 0));
2643 llvm::Value *TypeId =
2644 llvm::MetadataAsValue::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), MD);
2645
2646 llvm::Value *CastedVTable = Builder.CreateBitCast(VTable, Int8PtrTy);
2647 llvm::Value *TypeTest =
2648 Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::type_test),
2649 {CastedVTable, TypeId});
2650 Builder.CreateCall(CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::assume), TypeTest);
2651 }
2652}

2654void CodeGenFunction::EmitVTablePtrCheckForCall(const CXXRecordDecl *RD,
2655 llvm::Value *VTable,
2656 CFITypeCheckKind TCK,
2657 SourceLocation Loc) {
2658 if (!SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::CFICastStrict))
2659 RD = LeastDerivedClassWithSameLayout(RD);
2660
2661 EmitVTablePtrCheck(RD, VTable, TCK, Loc);

2663
2664void CodeGenFunction::EmitVTablePtrCheckForCast(QualType T,
2665 llvm::Value *Derived,
2666 bool MayBeNull,
2667 CFITypeCheckKind TCK,
2668 SourceLocation Loc) {
2669 if (!getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
2670 return;
2671
2672 auto *ClassTy = T->getAs<RecordType>();
2673 if (!ClassTy)
2674 return;
2675
2676 const CXXRecordDecl *ClassDecl = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(ClassTy->getDecl());
2677
2678 if (!ClassDecl->isCompleteDefinition() || !ClassDecl->isDynamicClass())
2679 return;
2680
2681 if (!SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::CFICastStrict))
2682 ClassDecl = LeastDerivedClassWithSameLayout(ClassDecl);
2683
2684 llvm::BasicBlock *ContBlock = nullptr;
2685
2686 if (MayBeNull) {
2687 llvm::Value *DerivedNotNull =
2688 Builder.CreateIsNotNull(Derived, "cast.nonnull");
2689
2690 llvm::BasicBlock *CheckBlock = createBasicBlock("cast.check");
2691 ContBlock = createBasicBlock("cast.cont");
2692
2693 Builder.CreateCondBr(DerivedNotNull, CheckBlock, ContBlock);
2694
2695 EmitBlock(CheckBlock);
2696 }
2697
2698 llvm::Value *VTable;
2699 std::tie(VTable, ClassDecl) = CGM.getCXXABI().LoadVTablePtr(
2700 *this, Address(Derived, getPointerAlign()), ClassDecl);
2701
2702 EmitVTablePtrCheck(ClassDecl, VTable, TCK, Loc);
2703
2704 if (MayBeNull) {
2705 Builder.CreateBr(ContBlock);
2706 EmitBlock(ContBlock);
2707 }
2708}
2709
2710void CodeGenFunction::EmitVTablePtrCheck(const CXXRecordDecl *RD,
2711 llvm::Value *VTable,
2712 CFITypeCheckKind TCK,
2713 SourceLocation Loc) {
2714 if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeCfiCrossDso &&
2715 !CGM.HasHiddenLTOVisibility(RD))
2716 return;
2717
2718 SanitizerMask M;
2719 llvm::SanitizerStatKind SSK;
2720 switch (TCK) {
2721 case CFITCK_VCall:
2722 M = SanitizerKind::CFIVCall;
2723 SSK = llvm::SanStat_CFI_VCall;
2724 break;
2725 case CFITCK_NVCall:
2726 M = SanitizerKind::CFINVCall;
2727 SSK = llvm::SanStat_CFI_NVCall;
2728 break;
2729 case CFITCK_DerivedCast:
2730 M = SanitizerKind::CFIDerivedCast;
2731 SSK = llvm::SanStat_CFI_DerivedCast;
2732 break;
2733 case CFITCK_UnrelatedCast:
2734 M = SanitizerKind::CFIUnrelatedCast;
2735 SSK = llvm::SanStat_CFI_UnrelatedCast;
2736 break;
2737 case CFITCK_ICall:
2738 case CFITCK_NVMFCall:
2739 case CFITCK_VMFCall:
2740 llvm_unreachable("unexpected sanitizer kind");
2741 }
2742
2743 std::string TypeName = RD->getQualifiedNameAsString();
2744 if (getContext().getSanitizerBlacklist().isBlacklistedType(M, TypeName))
2745 return;
2746
2747 SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
2748 EmitSanitizerStatReport(SSK);
2749
2750 llvm::Metadata *MD =
2751 CGM.CreateMetadataIdentifierForType(QualType(RD->getTypeForDecl(), 0));
2752 llvm::Value *TypeId = llvm::MetadataAsValue::get(getLLVMContext(), MD);
2753
2754 llvm::Value *CastedVTable = Builder.CreateBitCast(VTable, Int8PtrTy);
2755 llvm::Value *TypeTest = Builder.CreateCall(
2756 CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::type_test), {CastedVTable, TypeId});
2757
2758 llvm::Constant *StaticData[] = {
2759 llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int8Ty, TCK),
2760 EmitCheckSourceLocation(Loc),
2761 EmitCheckTypeDescriptor(QualType(RD->getTypeForDecl(), 0)),
2762 };
2763
2764 auto CrossDsoTypeId = CGM.CreateCrossDsoCfiTypeId(MD);
2765 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeCfiCrossDso && CrossDsoTypeId) {
2766 EmitCfiSlowPathCheck(M, TypeTest, CrossDsoTypeId, CastedVTable, StaticData);
2767 return;
2768 }
2769
2770 if (CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeTrap.has(M)) {
2771 EmitTrapCheck(TypeTest);
2772 return;
2773 }
2774
2775 llvm::Value *AllVtables = llvm::MetadataAsValue::get(
2776 CGM.getLLVMContext(),
2777 llvm::MDString::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), "all-vtables"));
2778 llvm::Value *ValidVtable = Builder.CreateCall(
2779 CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::type_test), {CastedVTable, AllVtables});
2780 EmitCheck(std::make_pair(TypeTest, M), SanitizerHandler::CFICheckFail,
2781 StaticData, {CastedVTable, ValidVtable});
2782}

2784bool CodeGenFunction::ShouldEmitVTableTypeCheckedLoad(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
2785 if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().WholeProgramVTables ||
2786 !SanOpts.has(SanitizerKind::CFIVCall) ||
2787 !CGM.getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeTrap.has(SanitizerKind::CFIVCall) ||
2788 !CGM.HasHiddenLTOVisibility(RD))
2789 return false;
2790
2791 std::string TypeName = RD->getQualifiedNameAsString();
2792 return !getContext().getSanitizerBlacklist().isBlacklistedType(
2793 SanitizerKind::CFIVCall, TypeName);
2794}

2796llvm::Value *CodeGenFunction::EmitVTableTypeCheckedLoad(
2797 const CXXRecordDecl *RD, llvm::Value *VTable, uint64_t VTableByteOffset) {
2798 SanitizerScope SanScope(this);
2799
2800 EmitSanitizerStatReport(llvm::SanStat_CFI_VCall);
2801
2802 llvm::Metadata *MD =
2803 CGM.CreateMetadataIdentifierForType(QualType(RD->getTypeForDecl(), 0));
2804 llvm::Value *TypeId = llvm::MetadataAsValue::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), MD);
2805
2806 llvm::Value *CastedVTable = Builder.CreateBitCast(VTable, Int8PtrTy);
2807 llvm::Value *CheckedLoad = Builder.CreateCall(
2808 CGM.getIntrinsic(llvm::Intrinsic::type_checked_load),
2809 {CastedVTable, llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, VTableByteOffset),
2810 TypeId});
2811 llvm::Value *CheckResult = Builder.CreateExtractValue(CheckedLoad, 1);
2812
2813 EmitCheck(std::make_pair(CheckResult, SanitizerKind::CFIVCall),
2814 SanitizerHandler::CFICheckFail, nullptr, nullptr);
2815
2816 return Builder.CreateBitCast(
2817 Builder.CreateExtractValue(CheckedLoad, 0),
2818 cast<llvm::PointerType>(VTable->getType())->getElementType());
2819}

2821void CodeGenFunction::EmitForwardingCallToLambda(
2822 const CXXMethodDecl *callOperator,
2823 CallArgList &callArgs) {
2824 // Get the address of the call operator.
2825 const CGFunctionInfo &calleeFnInfo =
2826 CGM.getTypes().arrangeCXXMethodDeclaration(callOperator);
2827 llvm::Constant *calleePtr =
2828 CGM.GetAddrOfFunction(GlobalDecl(callOperator),
2829 CGM.getTypes().GetFunctionType(calleeFnInfo));
2830
2831 // Prepare the return slot.
2832 const FunctionProtoType *FPT =
2833 callOperator->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
2834 QualType resultType = FPT->getReturnType();
2835 ReturnValueSlot returnSlot;
2836 if (!resultType->isVoidType() &&
2837 calleeFnInfo.getReturnInfo().getKind() == ABIArgInfo::Indirect &&
2838 !hasScalarEvaluationKind(calleeFnInfo.getReturnType()))
2839 returnSlot = ReturnValueSlot(ReturnValue, resultType.isVolatileQualified());
2840
2841 // We don't need to separately arrange the call arguments because
2842 // the call can't be variadic anyway --- it's impossible to forward
2843 // variadic arguments.
2844
2845 // Now emit our call.
2846 auto callee = CGCallee::forDirect(calleePtr, GlobalDecl(callOperator));
2847 RValue RV = EmitCall(calleeFnInfo, callee, returnSlot, callArgs);
2848
2849 // If necessary, copy the returned value into the slot.
2850 if (!resultType->isVoidType() && returnSlot.isNull()) {
2851 if (getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount && resultType->isObjCRetainableType()) {
2852 RV = RValue::get(EmitARCRetainAutoreleasedReturnValue(RV.getScalarVal()));
2853 }
2854 EmitReturnOfRValue(RV, resultType);
2855 } else
2856 EmitBranchThroughCleanup(ReturnBlock);
2857}

2859void CodeGenFunction::EmitLambdaBlockInvokeBody() {
2860 const BlockDecl *BD = BlockInfo->getBlockDecl();
2861 const VarDecl *variable = BD->capture_begin()->getVariable();
2862 const CXXRecordDecl *Lambda = variable->getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
2863 const CXXMethodDecl *CallOp = Lambda->getLambdaCallOperator();
2864
2865 if (CallOp->isVariadic()) {
2866 // FIXME: Making this work correctly is nasty because it requires either
2867 // cloning the body of the call operator or making the call operator
2868 // forward.
2869 CGM.ErrorUnsupported(CurCodeDecl, "lambda conversion to variadic function");
2870 return;
2871 }
2872
2873 // Start building arguments for forwarding call
2874 CallArgList CallArgs;
2875
2876 QualType ThisType = getContext().getPointerType(getContext().getRecordType(Lambda));
2877 Address ThisPtr = GetAddrOfBlockDecl(variable);
2878 CallArgs.add(
2879 RValue::get(ThisPtr.getPointer(), ThisPtr.getAlignment().getQuantity()),
2880 ThisType);
2881
2882 // Add the rest of the parameters.
2883 for (auto param : BD->parameters())
2884 EmitDelegateCallArg(CallArgs, param, param->getBeginLoc());
2885
2886 assert(!Lambda->isGenericLambda() &&
2887 "generic lambda interconversion to block not implemented");
2888 EmitForwardingCallToLambda(CallOp, CallArgs);
2889}
2890
2891void CodeGenFunction::EmitLambdaDelegatingInvokeBody(const CXXMethodDecl *MD) {
2892 const CXXRecordDecl *Lambda = MD->getParent();
2893
2894 // Start building arguments for forwarding call
2895 CallArgList CallArgs;
2896
2897 QualType ThisType = getContext().getPointerType(getContext().getRecordType(Lambda));
2898 llvm::Value *ThisPtr = llvm::UndefValue::get(getTypes().ConvertType(ThisType));
2899 CallArgs.add(RValue::get(ThisPtr), ThisType);
2900
2901 // Add the rest of the parameters.
2902 for (auto Param : MD->parameters())
2903 EmitDelegateCallArg(CallArgs, Param, Param->getBeginLoc());
2904
2905 const CXXMethodDecl *CallOp = Lambda->getLambdaCallOperator();
2906 // For a generic lambda, find the corresponding call operator specialization
2907 // to which the call to the static-invoker shall be forwarded.
2908 if (Lambda->isGenericLambda()) {
2909 assert(MD->isFunctionTemplateSpecialization());
2910 const TemplateArgumentList *TAL = MD->getTemplateSpecializationArgs();
2911 FunctionTemplateDecl *CallOpTemplate = CallOp->getDescribedFunctionTemplate();
2912 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
2913 FunctionDecl *CorrespondingCallOpSpecialization =
2914 CallOpTemplate->findSpecialization(TAL->asArray(), InsertPos);
2915 assert(CorrespondingCallOpSpecialization);
2916 CallOp = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(CorrespondingCallOpSpecialization);
2917 }
2918 EmitForwardingCallToLambda(CallOp, CallArgs);
2919}
2920
2921void CodeGenFunction::EmitLambdaStaticInvokeBody(const CXXMethodDecl *MD) {
2922 if (MD->isVariadic()) {
2923 // FIXME: Making this work correctly is nasty because it requires either
2924 // cloning the body of the call operator or making the call operator forward.
2925 CGM.ErrorUnsupported(MD, "lambda conversion to variadic function");
2926 return;
2927 }
2928
2929 EmitLambdaDelegatingInvokeBody(MD);
2930}
